Dacomitinib is typically prescribed for patients with advanced or metastatic NSCLC who have specific genetic mutations in their cancer cells. It is important to consult with a healthcare provider for more information about Dacomitinib, including its potential side effects and effectiveness for individual cases.

Dactinomycin, also known as actinomycin D, is a chemotherapy medication used to treat various types of cancer, including Wilms' tumor, gestational trophoblastic neoplasia, rhabdomyosarcoma, Ewing's sarcoma, and certain types of testicular cancer. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Dactinomycin is typically given as an injection into a vein by a healthcare provider in a hospital or clinic setting. Like all medications, dactinomycin can have side effects, so it's essential to discuss any concerns with your healthcare provider.

Danazol is a synthetic steroid derived from ethisterone that is used to treat endometriosis, fibrocystic breast disease, and hereditary angioedema. It works by suppressing the production of certain hormones involved in these conditions. Danazol can have side effects such as weight gain, acne, and mood changes. It is important to take this medication as prescribed by a healthcare provider and to discuss any concerns or side effects with them.

Daratumumab is a monoclonal antibody used in the treatment of multiple myeloma, a type of cancer that affects plasma cells in the bone marrow. It works by targeting a protein called CD38, which is found on the surface of myeloma cells, and helps the immune system to attack and kill these cancerous cells. Daratumumab has been shown to be effective in treating multiple myeloma, both as a standalone treatment and in combination with other medications. It is typically given as an intravenous infusion and may have some side effects, so it's important to discuss with your healthcare provider if you have any questions or concerns about this medication.

Darolutamide is a medication used in the treatment of prostate cancer. It belongs to a class of drugs known as androgen receptor inhibitors. Darolutamide works by blocking the effects of androgens (male hormones) on prostate cancer cells, helping to slow down the growth and spread of the cancer. It is typically used in combination with other treatments for advanced prostate cancer. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and discuss any potential side effects or concerns with them.

Dasatinib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, particularly chronic myeloid leukemia (CML) and acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ALL). It belongs to a class of drugs known as tyrosine kinase inhibitors, which work by blocking specific proteins that are involved in the growth and spread of cancer cells. Dasatinib is typically taken orally in the form of a tablet. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions carefully when taking dasatinib, as it can have side effects and interactions with other medications. If you have been prescribed dasatinib, make sure to discuss any questions or concerns with your healthcare provider.

Daunorubicin is a type of chemotherapy drug that belongs to a class of medications known as anthracyclines. It is commonly used in the treatment of various types of cancers, including leukemia, lymphoma, and breast cancer. Daunorubicin works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Like many chemotherapy drugs, daunorubicin can have side effects, such as nausea, vomiting, hair loss, and decreased blood cell counts. It is important for patients to discuss the potential benefits and risks of daunorubicin with their healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Daunorubicin liposomal is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as leukemia and lymphoma. It is a type of chemotherapy drug that works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. The liposomal formulation helps to improve the delivery of the medication to the cancer cells while reducing some of the side effects commonly associated with traditional daunorubicin. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of this medication with your healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Decitabine is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as myelodysplastic syndrome (MDS) and acute myeloid leukemia (AML). It works by helping to slow the growth of cancer cells in the body. Decitabine is typically given as an injection into a vein over a period of time. Like all medications, Decitabine can have side effects, so it is important to discuss any concerns with your healthcare provider.

Degarelix is a medication used in the treatment of advanced prostate cancer. It belongs to a class of drugs known as gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH) antagonists. Degarelix works by blocking the production of certain hormones that can stimulate the growth of prostate cancer cells. It is usually administered as an injection under the skin by a healthcare provider. As with any medication, there can be side effects and it is important to discuss the benefits and risks with your healthcare provider before starting treatment with Degarelix.

Denileukin diftitox is a medication used in the treatment of cutaneous T-cell lymphoma (CTCL), which is a type of non-Hodgkin's lymphoma. It works by targeting and destroying certain types of cancer cells. Denileukin diftitox is given through intravenous infusion and may cause side effects such as flu-like symptoms, skin reactions, and changes in blood counts. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of this medication with your healthcare provider.

Denosumab is a medication that is used to treat osteoporosis in postmenopausal women, as well as in men with osteoporosis. It works by inhibiting the activity of cells that break down bone, which helps to increase bone density and reduce the risk of fractures. Denosumab is typically given as an injection under the skin every 6 months. It is important to follow your doctor's recommendations and discuss any potential side effects or concerns with them.

Dexamethasone is a type of corticosteroid medication that has anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressant effects. It is commonly used to treat conditions such as inflammatory disorders, allergic reactions, autoimmune diseases, and certain types of cancer. Dexamethasone can be taken orally, injected into a muscle, or given intravenously depending on the condition being treated. It is important to follow the prescribed dosage and duration of treatment as directed by a healthcare professional, as prolonged use of dexamethasone can lead to side effects such as weight gain, high blood pressure, and increased risk of infections.

Dexrazoxane is a medication used to reduce the risk of heart damage in cancer patients who are receiving certain types of chemotherapy, specifically anthracyclines. Anthracyclines are known to cause heart damage as a side effect, and dexrazoxane works by protecting the heart from these harmful effects. It is usually given before each dose of anthracycline chemotherapy. Dexrazoxane is a cardioprotective agent and is prescribed by doctors to help prevent heart-related complications in cancer patients undergoing treatment.

Diethylstilbestrol (DES) is a synthetic form of estrogen that was prescribed to pregnant women in the mid-20th century to prevent miscarriages and other pregnancy complications. Unfortunately, it was later discovered that DES exposure in utero could lead to serious health issues for the offspring, such as an increased risk of certain cancers and reproductive system abnormalities. DES use during pregnancy has since been discontinued, and efforts have been made to inform those who may have been exposed to its potential risks.

Dinutuximab is a monoclonal antibody that is used in the treatment of high-risk neuroblastoma, a type of cancer that primarily affects children. It works by targeting and binding to a protein called GD2 that is found on the surface of neuroblastoma cells, which helps the immune system to recognize and destroy these cancer cells. Dinutuximab is usually given in combination with other treatments, such as chemotherapy and stem cell transplant, as part of a comprehensive treatment plan for neuroblastoma. It is important to discuss with your healthcare provider about the potential benefits and risks of dinutuximab treatment.

Docetaxel is a chemotherapy medication used to treat various types of cancer, including breast cancer, lung cancer, prostate cancer, and stomach cancer. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Docetaxel is usually given through an intravenous infusion in a healthcare setting. Like all chemotherapy drugs, it may have side effects, such as hair loss, nausea, vomiting, and decreased blood cell counts. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of docetaxel with your healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Doxifluridine is a medication used in the treatment of some types of cancer, such as stomach cancer and colorectal cancer. It belongs to a class of drugs known as fluoropyrimidines, which work by interfering with the growth of cancer cells. It is typically used in combination with other chemotherapy medications. As with any medication, it is important to follow your doctor's instructions and discuss any potential side effects or concerns with them.

Doxorubicin is a chemotherapy medication used to treat various types of cancer, including breast cancer, lung cancer, and leukemia. It works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells and is typically given as an injection into a vein. Doxorubicin can have side effects such as nausea, vomiting, hair loss, and increased risk of infections. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of doxorubicin treatment with a healthcare provider.

Durvalumab is a type of cancer treatment known as an immune checkpoint inhibitor. It works by helping the immune system recognize and attack cancer cells. It is used to treat various types of cancer, including lung cancer and bladder cancer. Durvalumab is typically administered through intravenous infusion and may cause side effects such as fatigue, cough, and skin rash. It is important to discuss the potential risks and benefits of Durvalumab with a healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Dutasteride is a medication used to treat benign prostatic hyperplasia (enlarged prostate) and male pattern hair loss. It works by inhibiting the production of a hormone that contributes to prostate enlargement and hair loss. Dutasteride is available in oral capsule form and should be taken as prescribed by a healthcare provider. It is important to discuss any potential side effects and risks with a doctor before starting treatment with Dutasteride.

Duvelisib is a medication used to treat certain types of cancer, specifically chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL) and small lymphocytic lymphoma (SLL). It works by blocking certain proteins in the body that promote the growth of cancer cells. Duvelisib is typically used when other treatments have not been effective or have stopped working. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of Duvelisib with your healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Edrecolomab is a monoclonal antibody that was studied as a potential treatment for certain types of cancer, specifically colorectal cancer. It was designed to target and bind to a protein called Ep-CAM, which is found on the surface of some cancer cells. However, clinical trials of Edrecolomab did not show significant enough benefits in terms of patient outcomes, and it is not currently approved for use in the treatment of cancer. Research into new and more effective cancer treatments continues, with a focus on different types of immunotherapy and targeted therapies.

Elotuzumab is a monoclonal antibody used in the treatment of multiple myeloma, a type of cancer that affects plasma cells in the bone marrow. It works by targeting a protein called SLAMF7, which is found on myeloma cells, helping the immune system to attack and kill these cancerous cells. Elotuzumab is often used in combination with other medications for the treatment of multiple myeloma. It is important to consult with a healthcare provider for more information about this medication and its potential side effects.

Enasidenib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of leukemia. It is specifically used for the treatment of acute myeloid leukemia (AML) in adults who have a specific genetic mutation known as IDH2. Enasidenib works by targeting and inhibiting this mutated protein, which can help to slow down or stop the growth of cancer cells. It is typically prescribed by a healthcare provider and is taken in the form of oral tablets. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and discuss any questions or concerns you may have.

Encorafenib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as melanoma. It is a type of medication known as a kinase inhibitor, which works by targeting specific proteins in cancer cells to help slow down or stop their growth. Encorafenib is typically used in combination with other medications or treatments as part of a comprehensive cancer treatment plan. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and guidance while taking Encorafenib.

Entrectinib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, specifically non-small cell lung cancer and certain types of solid tumors that have a specific genetic mutation. It works by targeting and inhibiting specific proteins involved in the growth and spread of cancer cells. It is usually prescribed by a healthcare provider and may have side effects that should be discussed with a doctor.

Enzalutamide is a medication used in the treatment of prostate cancer. It belongs to a class of drugs known as androgen receptor inhibitors. Enzalutamide works by blocking the effect of the male hormones (androgens) on the prostate cancer cells, thereby slowing down the growth and spread of the cancer. It is typically prescribed for patients with advanced prostate cancer that has spread to other parts of the body. As with any medication, it is important to follow your doctor's instructions and report any side effects or concerns while taking Enzalutamide.

Epirubicin is a type of chemotherapy drug used in the treatment of various cancers, including breast cancer, stomach cancer, and lung cancer. It belongs to a class of medications known as anthracyclines, which work by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Epirubicin is usually given as an intravenous infusion in a clinical setting under the supervision of healthcare professionals. Like all chemotherapy drugs, it can cause side effects, which may include nausea, vomiting, hair loss, and increased risk of infections. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of treatment with Epirubicin with your healthcare provider.

Erdafitinib is a medication used to treat certain types of advanced or metastatic bladder cancer that have specific genetic mutations. It is a type of targeted therapy known as a fibroblast growth factor receptor (FGFR) inhibitor. Erdafitinib works by blocking abnormal FGFR proteins in cancer cells, which can help slow down or stop the growth of the cancer. It is typically prescribed by a doctor and is taken orally in the form of tablets. As with any medication, Erdafitinib may have side effects and should be used under the supervision of a healthcare provider.

Eribulin is a chemotherapy medication used to treat advanced breast cancer and liposarcoma. It works by disrupting the growth of cancer cells, ultimately leading to their death. Eribulin is usually given by injection into a vein and can have various side effects, such as fatigue, nausea, low white blood cell count, and hair loss. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of Eribulin with a healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Erlotinib is a medication used to treat certain types of lung cancer and pancreatic cancer. It belongs to a class of drugs known as tyrosine kinase inhibitors, which work by blocking the action of a protein that is involved in the growth and spread of cancer cells. Erlotinib is typically taken orally as a tablet and is commonly prescribed in combination with other cancer treatments. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and discuss any potential side effects or concerns.

Estramustine is a medication that is used in the treatment of prostate cancer. It is a combination of estradiol, a form of estrogen, and nitrogen mustard, a type of chemotherapy agent. Estramustine works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells in the prostate. It is typically used in combination with other medications or treatments for prostate cancer. As with any medication, it is important to follow your doctor's instructions carefully and be aware of potential side effects and interactions.

Etoposide is a medication commonly used in cancer treatment, particularly for certain types of leukemia, lung cancer, testicular cancer, and ovarian cancer. It belongs to a class of medications known as topoisomerase inhibitors, which work by interfering with the enzymes that help cells divide and grow. Etoposide is typically administered intravenously in a hospital setting and can have side effects such as nausea, vomiting, hair loss, and a decrease in blood cell counts. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions closely when taking etoposide.

Everolimus is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as mTOR inhibitors. It is commonly used to treat certain types of cancers, including breast cancer, kidney cancer, and pancreatic neuroendocrine tumors. Everolimus works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells and slowing down their spread in the body. It is usually taken in the form of a tablet and is available by prescription only. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and discuss any potential side effects or concerns with them.

Exemestane is a medication used to treat breast cancer in postmenopausal women. It belongs to a class of drugs known as aromatase inhibitors, which work by reducing the production of estrogen in the body. This helps to slow down or stop the growth of hormone-receptor-positive breast cancer cells. Exemestane is typically taken orally in tablet form and is often prescribed as part of a comprehensive treatment plan for breast cancer. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when taking Exemestane and to report any side effects or concerns during treatment.

Floxuridine is a chemotherapy medication used to treat various types of cancer, including colorectal cancer. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Floxuridine is typically administered intravenously in a clinical setting under the supervision of healthcare professionals. Like all chemotherapy drugs, Floxuridine can cause side effects, which may vary from person to person. It's important to discuss any concerns or questions about Floxuridine with a healthcare provider.

Fludarabine is a chemotherapy drug used to treat certain types of cancer, including chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL), non-Hodgkin lymphoma, and certain types of leukemia. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Fludarabine may be given alone or in combination with other chemotherapy drugs. It is typically administered intravenously in a hospital or clinic setting. Like all chemotherapy drugs, fludarabine has potential side effects, which can vary from person to person. It's important to discuss the risks and benefits of fludarabine treatment with your healthcare provider.

Fluorouracil, also known by the brand name Adrucil, is a medication used in the treatment of various types of cancer, including skin, breast, and gastrointestinal cancers. It belongs to a class of medications known as antimetabolites, which work by interfering with the growth of cancer cells. Fluorouracil is typically administered intravenously or topically, depending on the type and stage of cancer being treated. It is important to follow the prescribed dosage and schedule and to discuss any potential side effects with your healthcare provider.

Fluoxymesterone is a synthetic androgen and anabolic steroid. It is sold under the brand name Halotestin and is used to treat delayed puberty in males and breast cancer in women. It is also used illicitly by athletes and bodybuilders to enhance performance and muscle growth. However, it can have serious side effects, including liver toxicity, cardiovascular issues, and hormonal imbalances. It is a controlled substance and should only be used under the supervision of a healthcare professional.

Flutamide is a medication used in the treatment of prostate cancer. It belongs to a class of drugs known as antiandrogens, which work by blocking the action of male sex hormones in the body. Flutamide is often used in combination with other medications or treatments to help manage prostate cancer. It is important to take Flutamide exactly as prescribed by a healthcare provider and to discuss any potential side effects or concerns with a doctor.

Folinic acid, also known as leucovorin, is a form of folic acid that is often used as a supplement in the treatment of certain types of anemia and in people with folic acid deficiencies. It is also used in combination with certain medications to help treat certain types of cancer, such as colorectal cancer. Folinic acid is a water-soluble vitamin that plays a key role in many important functions in the body, including cell division and the synthesis of DNA. It is generally considered safe when taken in appropriate doses, but as with any supplement, it is important to consult with a healthcare provider before starting any new treatment regimen.

Formestane is an aromatase inhibitor, which means it helps lower estrogen levels in the body. It is commonly used in bodybuilding to reduce estrogen levels and increase testosterone production. However, it is important to note that the use of Formestane for non-medical purposes can have potential side effects and risks, so it is essential to consult with a healthcare professional before using it.

Forodesine is a drug that belongs to a class of medications known as purine nucleoside phosphorylase (PNP) inhibitors. It is being studied for its potential use in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as T-cell lymphoma and leukemia. Forodesine works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells. It is still in the experimental stage and more research is needed to determine its safety and effectiveness.

Fostamatinib is a medication used to treat chronic immune thrombocytopenia (ITP), a condition where the immune system mistakenly attacks and destroys platelets, which are necessary for blood clotting. Fostamatinib works by inhibiting an enzyme involved in the production of antibodies that attack platelets. It is taken in tablet form and is typically prescribed when other treatments for ITP have not been effective. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and discuss any potential side effects or concerns.

Fotemustine is a chemotherapy medication used to treat certain types of brain tumors, such as malignant melanoma and glioma. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Fotemustine is typically given intravenously by a healthcare provider in a hospital setting. Like all chemotherapy drugs, Fotemustine can cause side effects, so it is important to discuss potential risks and benefits with your healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Fulvestrant is a medication used in the treatment of hormone receptor-positive breast cancer in postmenopausal women. It belongs to a class of drugs known as estrogen receptor antagonists. Fulvestrant works by binding to estrogen receptors and blocking the effects of estrogen on cancer cells, thereby slowing down or stopping the growth of the tumor. It is usually given as an injection into the muscle. Like any medication, Fulvestrant may have side effects, so it is important to discuss them with your healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Gefitinib is a medication used in the treatment of non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC). It belongs to a class of drugs known as tyrosine kinase inhibitors, which work by blocking signals within cancer cells that help them grow and spread. Gefitinib is often prescribed for patients with NSCLC that has certain genetic mutations, such as EGFR mutations. It is usually taken orally in the form of tablets. As with any medication, Gefitinib may have side effects, so it's important to discuss them with your healthcare provider.

Gemcitabine is a chemotherapy medication used to treat various types of cancer, including pancreatic cancer, lung cancer, breast cancer, and ovarian cancer. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Gemcitabine is usually given through intravenous infusion in a healthcare setting under the supervision of a healthcare provider. Side effects may include nausea, vomiting, fatigue, and lowered blood cell counts. It is important to discuss any concerns or questions about gemcitabine with your healthcare provider.

Gemtuzumab ozogamicin is a medication used to treat certain types of acute myeloid leukemia (AML). It is a type of targeted therapy known as an antibody-drug conjugate. Gemtuzumab ozogamicin works by attaching to a protein on the surface of leukemia cells and delivering a toxic substance directly to the cancer cells, causing them to die. It is typically used in combination with other chemotherapy drugs for the treatment of AML in adults. As with any medication, there are potential side effects and risks associated with gemtuzumab ozogamicin, so it is important to discuss these with your healthcare provider.

Gilteritinib is a medication used for the treatment of certain types of leukemia, specifically acute myeloid leukemia (AML) with a FLT3 mutation. It works by inhibiting the activity of the FLT3 protein, which can help slow down the growth and spread of cancer cells. Gilteritinib may be prescribed by healthcare providers as part of a treatment plan for patients with AML. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and guidance while taking this medication.

Glasdegib is a medication that is used in combination with low-dose cytarabine to treat newly diagnosed acute myeloid leukemia (AML) in adult patients who are not eligible for intensive chemotherapy. It is a type of medication known as a hedgehog pathway inhibitor, which works by blocking a specific signaling pathway that is believed to play a role in the growth of certain types of cancer cells. As with any medication, it is important to discuss with your healthcare provider about the potential benefits and risks of using Glasdegib.

Goserelin is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH) agonists. It is used to treat various conditions such as prostate cancer, breast cancer, endometriosis, and certain gynecological disorders. Goserelin works by decreasing the production of certain hormones in the body, which can help slow down or stop the growth of cancer cells or manage symptoms of certain conditions. It is typically given as an injection under the skin or into a muscle by a healthcare provider. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when taking this medication and to discuss any concerns or side effects with them.

Histrelin is a synthetic hormone that is used in medicine to treat conditions such as advanced prostate cancer, endometriosis, and central precocious puberty. It works by decreasing the production of certain hormones in the body. Histrelin is typically administered as an implant placed under the skin, releasing the medication gradually over a period of months to provide continuous treatment. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions carefully when using Histrelin and to discuss any potential side effects or concerns with them.

Hydrocortisone is a type of corticosteroid medication that is used to reduce inflammation and itching associated with various skin conditions such as eczema, dermatitis, and insect bites. It works by decreasing the body's immune response to reduce swelling, redness, and itching. Hydrocortisone is available in different forms including creams, ointments, lotions, and sprays, and is usually applied directly to the affected skin area. It is important to use hydrocortisone as directed by a healthcare provider to avoid potential side effects associated with prolonged use.

Hydroxyurea is a medication that is used to treat certain types of cancer, such as chronic myeloid leukemia, ovarian cancer, and certain types of skin cancer. It works by slowing down or stopping the growth of cancer cells in the body. Hydroxyurea is also used to treat sickle cell anemia and certain other blood disorders. It is important to take this medication exactly as prescribed by your doctor and to follow their instructions closely. Like all medications, hydroxyurea can have side effects, so it is important to discuss the risks and benefits with your healthcare provider.

Ibritumomab tiuxetan is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of non-Hodgkin's lymphoma. It is a type of targeted therapy called radioimmunotherapy, which combines a monoclonal antibody with a radioactive isotope. The monoclonal antibody targets specific proteins on cancer cells, allowing the radioactive isotope to deliver radiation directly to the cancer cells. This can help to destroy the cancer cells while minimizing damage to healthy cells. It is typically used in patients with relapsed or refractory low-grade or follicular B-cell non-Hodgkin's lymphoma. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of this treatment with your healthcare provider.

Ibrutinib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL), mantle cell lymphoma (MCL), and Waldenstrom's macroglobulinemia. It works by blocking certain proteins in cancer cells, which helps to slow down or stop the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Ibrutinib is typically taken orally in the form of a pill and is available by prescription only. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions carefully when taking this medication.

Icotinib is a medication used for the treatment of non-small cell lung cancer. It belongs to a class of medications known as epidermal growth factor receptor (EGFR) tyrosine kinase inhibitors. Icotinib works by blocking certain proteins in cancer cells, which can slow down or stop the growth of the cancer. It is typically used in patients who have EGFR-mutated non-small cell lung cancer that has not responded to other treatments. As with any medication, it is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks with your healthcare provider.

Idarubicin is a type of chemotherapy medication used to treat certain types of cancers, such as leukemia. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Idarubicin belongs to a class of drugs known as anthracyclines. It is typically administered intravenously by a healthcare provider in a hospital or clinic setting. Like all chemotherapy drugs, Idarubicin can have side effects, so it's important to discuss them with your healthcare team.

Idelalisib is a medication used to treat certain types of blood cancers, specifically chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL) and follicular lymphoma. It belongs to a class of drugs called kinase inhibitors, which work by blocking signals that cancer cells need to grow. Idelalisib is typically used when other treatments have not been effective or if the cancer has come back after previous treatment. As with any medication, it is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks with your healthcare provider.

Ifosfamide is a medication used in chemotherapy to treat various types of cancer, including testicular cancer, ovarian cancer, and soft tissue sarcomas. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Ifosfamide is usually given intravenously in a hospital or clinic setting under the supervision of a healthcare provider. Like all chemotherapy drugs, Ifosfamide can have side effects, and it is important for patients to discuss these with their healthcare team before starting treatment.

Imatinib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as chronic myeloid leukemia (CML) and gastrointestinal stromal tumors (GIST). It belongs to a class of drugs called tyrosine kinase inhibitors, which work by blocking the action of specific proteins involved in the growth of cancer cells. Imatinib has been shown to be effective in slowing down or stopping the progression of these types of cancers and has helped improve the outcomes for many patients. It is usually taken orally in the form of a tablet. As with any medication, it is important to follow the dosage and administration instructions provided by a healthcare professional.

Infigratinib is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as fibroblast growth factor receptor (FGFR) inhibitors. It is used for the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as cholangiocarcinoma and urothelial carcinoma, that have specific genetic mutations involving the FGFR gene. Infigratinib works by blocking the activity of these mutated FGFR proteins, which can help slow down or stop the growth of cancer cells. As with any medication, it is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of infigratinib with a healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Inotuzumab ozogamicin is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of leukemia, specifically acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ALL). It is a type of targeted therapy known as an antibody-drug conjugate, which works by targeting leukemia cells and delivering a potent chemotherapy drug directly to them. This can help to destroy cancer cells while minimizing damage to healthy cells. Inotuzumab ozogamicin is typically used when other treatments have not been effective or have stopped working. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of this medication with your healthcare provider.

Interferon alfa-2a is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as interferons. It is used to treat certain types of cancers, such as hairy cell leukemia, melanoma, and certain types of lymphoma. Interferon alfa-2a works by helping the immune system fight cancer cells. It can also be used to treat certain viral infections, such as hepatitis B and C. Like all medications, Interferon alfa-2a may cause side effects, so it is important to discuss the risks and benefits with your healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Interferon alfa-2b is a type of medication known as a biologic response modifier. It is a synthetic version of a substance naturally produced by the body in response to viral infections. Interferon alfa-2b is used to treat various conditions, including certain types of cancer (such as melanoma, hairy cell leukemia, and Kaposi's sarcoma), viral infections (such as hepatitis B and C), and autoimmune diseases (such as multiple sclerosis). It works by boosting the body's immune response to help fight off these conditions. Like any medication, Interferon alfa-2b can have side effects, so it is important to discuss with your healthcare provider before starting this treatment.

Interferon gamma-1b is a medication used to treat chronic granulomatous disease and severe malignant osteopetrosis. It is a synthetic version of a protein called interferon gamma, which helps the immune system fight off infections and regulate immune responses. This medication is typically given by injection under the skin or into a muscle. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when taking Interferon gamma-1b and to report any side effects or concerns to them.

Ipilimumab is a type of immunotherapy drug used in the treatment of certain types of cancers, such as melanoma. It works by activating the immune system to target and attack cancer cells. Ipilimumab is often used in combination with other cancer treatments to help improve outcomes for patients. As with any medication, it may have side effects, so it's important to discuss the risks and benefits with a healthcare provider.

Irinotecan is a chemotherapy drug used to treat various types of cancer, including colorectal cancer. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Common side effects of irinotecan include nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, and low blood cell counts. It is important to discuss any questions or concerns about irinotecan with your healthcare provider.

Irinotecan liposome is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, including metastatic pancreatic cancer. It is a form of irinotecan, a chemotherapy drug, that is encapsulated in liposomes to help improve its delivery and effectiveness in the body. Irinotecan liposome works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells. Like any medication, it may have side effects, so it is important to discuss with your healthcare provider about the potential benefits and risks of using this treatment.

Isatuximab is a monoclonal antibody that is used in the treatment of multiple myeloma, a type of cancer that affects plasma cells in the bone marrow. It works by targeting a protein called CD38, which is found on the surface of myeloma cells, and helps to activate the immune system to attack and destroy these cancerous cells. Isatuximab is typically used in combination with other medications for the treatment of multiple myeloma. It is important to consult with a healthcare provider for more information about Isatuximab and its potential benefits and side effects.

Isotretinoin, also known by the brand name Accutane, is a medication primarily used to treat severe acne that has not responded to other treatments. It is a powerful oral medication that works by reducing the production of oil by the skin's oil glands. Isotretinoin is highly effective in treating severe acne, but it can also have potentially serious side effects, so it is usually prescribed only when other treatments have failed. It is important to take isotretinoin exactly as prescribed and to follow up with your healthcare provider regularly while taking the medication.

Ivosidenib is a medication used to treat a type of blood cancer called acute myeloid leukemia (AML). It works by blocking a specific enzyme that is often mutated in AML, which helps to slow down the growth of cancer cells. Ivosidenib is typically prescribed for adults who have not responded to other treatments or who are not eligible for intensive chemotherapy. It is important to discuss with your healthcare provider about the potential benefits and risks of using Ivosidenib for your specific condition.

Ixabepilone is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as breast cancer. It belongs to a class of drugs called epothilones, which work by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. It is typically given through injection and is used when other treatments have not been effective. As with any medication, it is important to discuss potential side effects and benefits with your healthcare provider.

Ixazomib is a medication used in the treatment of multiple myeloma, a type of cancer that affects plasma cells in the bone marrow. It belongs to a class of drugs called proteasome inhibitors, which work by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells. Ixazomib is typically prescribed in combination with other medications for treating multiple myeloma. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when taking ixazomib and to report any side effects or concerns to them.

Ketoconazole is an antifungal medication used to treat fungal infections such as athlete's foot, jock itch, ringworm, and certain types of dandruff. It works by inhibiting the growth of fungi. Ketoconazole can be found in topical forms such as creams, shampoos, and foams, as well as in oral tablets for more severe infections. It is important to use ketoconazole as directed by a healthcare professional to ensure its effectiveness and minimize potential side effects.

Lanreotide is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs called somatostatin analogs. It is used to treat certain conditions such as acromegaly (a hormonal disorder that results in enlarged hands, feet, and face) and neuroendocrine tumors. Lanreotide works by reducing the production of certain hormones in the body, which helps to alleviate symptoms associated with these conditions. It is usually given as an injection under the skin and the frequency of dosing can vary depending on the individual's condition and response to the medication. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and discuss any questions or concerns you may have.

Lansoprazole is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as proton pump inhibitors (PPIs). It is commonly used to treat conditions such as gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD), stomach ulcers, and Zollinger-Ellison syndrome. Lansoprazole works by reducing the amount of acid produced in the stomach, which helps to alleviate symptoms such as heartburn, acid indigestion, and stomach pain. It is available both by prescription and over-the-counter in some countries. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and discuss any potential side effects or interactions with other medications.

Lapatinib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of breast cancer. It is a targeted therapy drug that works by blocking the action of certain proteins that are involved in the growth of cancer cells. Lapatinib is typically used in combination with other medications or treatments for breast cancer, and it is important to follow your doctor's recommendations when taking this medication. As with any medication, there may be side effects associated with lapatinib, so it is important to discuss any concerns with your healthcare provider.

Larotrectinib is a targeted therapy used to treat certain types of cancers that have a specific genetic alteration called an NTRK gene fusion. It is used in the treatment of solid tumors in both adults and children. Larotrectinib works by inhibiting the activity of the NTRK proteins, which can help slow down or stop the growth of cancer cells. It is considered a promising treatment option for patients with NTRK fusion-positive cancers. As with any medication, it is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of Larotrectinib with your healthcare provider.

Lenalidomide is a medication used in the treatment of certain cancers, such as multiple myeloma and myelodysplastic syndromes. It is a type of immunomodulatory drug that works by helping the immune system attack cancer cells. Lenalidomide is typically taken orally in the form of a capsule. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when taking this medication, as it can have side effects and interactions with other drugs.

Lenograstim is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as granulocyte colony-stimulating factors (G-CSF). It is used to stimulate the production of white blood cells in patients undergoing chemotherapy or bone marrow transplantation. Lenograstim helps reduce the risk of infection by boosting the immune system and promoting the growth of white blood cells. It is typically given by injection under the skin or into a vein. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and discuss any questions or concerns you may have.

Lenvatinib is a medication used to treat certain types of cancer, including thyroid cancer and liver cancer. It works by slowing or stopping the growth of cancer cells in the body. Lenvatinib is usually taken orally in the form of a tablet and is available under the brand name Lenvima. As with any medication, it is important to follow your doctor's instructions and report any side effects that you may experience while taking Lenvatinib.

Letrozole is a medication commonly used to treat breast cancer in postmenopausal women. It belongs to a class of drugs known as aromatase inhibitors, which work by reducing the production of estrogen in the body. By lowering estrogen levels, Letrozole helps to slow or stop the growth of hormone receptor-positive breast cancer cells. It is usually taken orally once a day and may have side effects such as hot flashes, fatigue, and joint pain. It is important to take Letrozole exactly as prescribed by a healthcare provider and to discuss any concerns or side effects with a medical professional.

Leuprolide is a medication used in the treatment of various conditions such as prostate cancer, endometriosis, uterine fibroids, and precocious puberty. It works by decreasing the production of certain hormones in the body. Leuprolide is typically given as an injection and should be administered by a healthcare professional. It is important to follow the dosage and instructions provided by your healthcare provider when taking Leuprolide. Like all medications, Leuprolide may have side effects, so it is important to discuss any concerns with your healthcare provider.

Levamisole is a medication used to treat parasitic worm infections in humans and animals. It works by paralyzing the worms, making it easier for the body to eliminate them. In some cases, Levamisole has also been used off-label to treat certain autoimmune conditions like rheumatoid arthritis. However, it is important to use Levamisole only under the guidance of a healthcare professional due to its potential side effects and interactions with other medications.

Levoleucovorin is a medication that is used to prevent or treat severe low levels of folic acid in the body. It is often given in combination with certain chemotherapy drugs to reduce their side effects and improve their effectiveness. Levoleucovorin is a prescription medication and should only be used under the supervision of a healthcare provider. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when taking this medication.

Lomustine, also known as CCNU, is a chemotherapy medication used to treat certain types of cancer, including brain tumors, Hodgkin's lymphoma, and some types of leukemia. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Lomustine is typically taken as a capsule by mouth, and the dosage and frequency of administration will depend on the specific type of cancer being treated. As with any medication, there may be side effects associated with lomustine, and it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and report any unusual symptoms or side effects.

Lorlatinib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, specifically non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC). It belongs to a class of drugs known as tyrosine kinase inhibitors, which work by blocking specific proteins involved in the growth and spread of cancer cells. Lorlatinib is typically prescribed for patients who have a specific genetic mutation called ALK or ROS1 rearrangement. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and guidance while taking Lorlatinib, as it may cause side effects and interactions with other medications.

Lutetium Lu 177 dotatate, also known as Lutathera, is a radiopharmaceutical used for the treatment of certain types of neuroendocrine tumors. It contains the radioisotope Lutetium-177, which emits beta particles that can target and destroy cancer cells. Lutetium Lu 177 dotatate is typically administered via intravenous infusion and is considered a targeted therapy for patients with inoperable or metastatic neuroendocrine tumors. As with any cancer treatment, it is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks with your healthcare provider.

Tafasitamab is a monoclonal antibody used in the treatment of certain types of lymphoma, specifically diffuse large B-cell lymphoma (DLBCL). It works by targeting a specific protein on the surface of cancer cells, helping the immune system to recognize and attack these cells. Tafasitamab is often used in combination with other cancer treatments. As with any medication, it is important to discuss potential side effects and benefits with your healthcare provider.

Mechlorethamine, also known as mustine, is a chemotherapy medication used to treat various types of cancer, such as Hodgkin's lymphoma, non-Hodgkin's lymphoma, and certain types of leukemia. It is classified as an alkylating agent and works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells. Mechlorethamine is typically administered intravenously by a healthcare professional in a clinical setting due to its potential side effects and toxicity. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and closely monitor for any adverse reactions while receiving treatment with Mechlorethamine.

Medroxyprogesterone is a synthetic form of the hormone progesterone. It is commonly used in women to treat menstrual disorders, such as irregular periods or abnormal uterine bleeding. It is also used as a contraceptive, to help regulate the menstrual cycle, and in hormone replacement therapy. Medroxyprogesterone works by mimicking the effects of progesterone in the body. It is typically taken orally or by injection under the supervision of a healthcare provider. Like any medication, it may have side effects and interactions with other drugs, so it's important to use it as directed and consult with a healthcare professional.

Megestrol is a medication that is used for various conditions, including the treatment of breast cancer, appetite stimulation in cancer patients, and as a contraceptive. It works by affecting hormone levels in the body. It is important to take this medication exactly as prescribed by a healthcare provider and to be aware of any potential side effects or interactions with other medications.

Melphalan is a type of chemotherapy medication that is used to treat certain types of cancer, such as multiple myeloma and ovarian cancer. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Melphalan is typically given as an injection or taken orally in tablet form. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions carefully when taking melphalan, as it can have side effects and interactions with other medications. It is always best to discuss any concerns or questions about melphalan with your healthcare provider.

Mercaptopurine is a medication commonly used to treat certain types of cancer, such as leukemia. It belongs to a class of medications known as antimetabolites, which work by interfering with the growth of cancer cells in the body. Mercaptopurine is often used in combination with other chemotherapy drugs to improve its effectiveness in treating cancer. It is important to take Mercaptopurine exactly as prescribed by a healthcare provider, as it can have serious side effects if not used properly. Common side effects of Mercaptopurine may include nausea, vomiting, loss of appetite, and lowered blood cell counts. It is important to discuss any concerns or questions about Mercaptopurine with a healthcare provider.

Mesna is a medication used to prevent or reduce the risk of bladder irritation and bleeding that may be caused by certain chemotherapy drugs. It works by binding to and inactivating harmful metabolites produced by these drugs, protecting the bladder lining. Mesna is commonly used in cancer treatment, particularly for drugs like ifosfamide and cyclophosphamide. It is usually given by injection or taken by mouth under the supervision of a healthcare provider. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when taking Mesna to ensure its effectiveness and minimize potential side effects.

Methotrexate is a medication commonly used to treat various conditions such as cancer, autoimmune diseases like rheumatoid arthritis, psoriasis, and inflammatory bowel disease. It works by interfering with the growth of certain cells in the body, particularly rapidly dividing cells like cancer cells and cells of the immune system. It is usually taken as a tablet or injection and must be used under the guidance of a healthcare provider due to potential side effects and the need for monitoring. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions closely while taking Methotrexate.

Methoxsalen is a medication that is used in combination with ultraviolet light therapy to treat certain skin conditions such as psoriasis, eczema, and vitiligo. It works by sensitizing the skin to ultraviolet light, which helps to slow down the growth of skin cells and reduce inflammation. Methoxsalen is available in oral and topical forms and should be used under the guidance of a healthcare provider due to potential side effects and risks associated with UV exposure. It is important to follow the instructions provided by your healthcare provider when using Methoxsalen.

Methylprednisolone is a corticosteroid medication that is used to treat various conditions such as inflammation, allergies, autoimmune disorders, and certain types of cancer. It works by reducing inflammation and suppressing the immune system. Methylprednisolone can be taken orally, by injection, or through intravenous infusion. It is important to follow the prescribed dosage and duration of treatment as directed by a healthcare professional, as misuse or abrupt discontinuation of the medication can lead to side effects. Common side effects may include increased appetite, weight gain, insomnia, and mood changes. It is important to discuss any concerns or questions about methylprednisolone with a healthcare provider.

Midostaurin is a medication that is used to treat certain types of blood cancers, specifically acute myeloid leukemia (AML) and advanced systemic mastocytosis. It belongs to a class of drugs called kinase inhibitors, which work by blocking the action of abnormal proteins that can cause cancer cells to grow and multiply. Midostaurin is usually taken in combination with other chemotherapy drugs and is available in capsule form. It is important to take Midostaurin exactly as prescribed by your healthcare provider and to follow all instructions for monitoring and managing any potential side effects.

Mitomycin is a type of chemotherapy medication that is used to treat certain types of cancer, such as stomach, pancreatic, lung, and bladder cancer. It works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells in the body. Mitomycin is typically given as an injection by a healthcare provider in a medical setting. It can have side effects such as nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, and a decreased white blood cell count. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and report any side effects you may experience while taking Mitomycin.

Mitotane, also known by the brand name Lysodren, is a medication used in the treatment of adrenocortical carcinoma, a type of cancer that affects the adrenal glands. Mitotane works by destroying the outer layer of the adrenal glands, where the cancerous cells are located. It is usually taken orally and may be used alone or in combination with other cancer treatments. Mitotane can have side effects such as nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, and dizziness, so it is important to take it as prescribed by a healthcare provider and to report any side effects promptly.

Mitoxantrone is a type of chemotherapy medication used to treat certain types of cancer, such as leukemia, lymphoma, and breast cancer. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Mitoxantrone is typically given intravenously by a healthcare professional in a medical setting. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions carefully when receiving this medication, as it can have serious side effects. If you have any specific questions or concerns about Mitoxantrone, it is best to discuss them with your healthcare provider.

Mogamulizumab is a monoclonal antibody used in the treatment of certain types of T-cell lymphomas, such as cutaneous T-cell lymphoma (CTCL) and peripheral T-cell lymphoma (PTCL). It works by targeting a protein called CC chemokine receptor 4 (CCR4) found on the surface of cancerous T-cells, which helps to destroy the cancer cells and inhibit their growth. Mogamulizumab is typically used in patients who have not responded to other treatments or have relapsed after previous therapies. It is administered intravenously and may have side effects such as infusion reactions, skin rashes, and infections. It's important to discuss with a healthcare provider about the benefits and potential risks of using mogamulizumab for your specific condition.

Moxetumomab pasudotox is a medication used in the treatment of hairy cell leukemia, a rare type of blood cancer. It is a recombinant immunotoxin that works by targeting and killing cancer cells that express the CD22 antigen. This medication is typically used when other treatments have not been effective. As with any medication, it is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks with your healthcare provider.

Nadroparin is a type of medication known as a low molecular weight heparin. It is used to prevent and treat blood clots in conditions such as deep vein thrombosis, pulmonary embolism, and during certain medical procedures like surgery. Nadroparin works by inhibiting the formation of blood clots. It is typically administered via injection under the skin. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and report any side effects or concerns while taking Nadroparin.

Necitumumab is a type of medication known as a monoclonal antibody that is used in the treatment of advanced squamous non-small cell lung cancer. It works by targeting a protein called epidermal growth factor receptor (EGFR) to help slow down or stop the growth of cancer cells. It is typically used in combination with other chemotherapy drugs for this type of cancer. As with any medication, there can be side effects and it's important to discuss with your healthcare provider if Necitumumab is a suitable treatment option for you.

Nedaplatin is a chemotherapy drug that is used to treat various types of cancer, including lung cancer, ovarian cancer, and bladder cancer. It belongs to a class of drugs known as platinum-based chemotherapy agents, which work by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Nedaplatin is often used in combination with other chemotherapy drugs to improve treatment outcomes. As with any chemotherapy drug, Nedaplatin can have side effects, so it is important to discuss the potential risks and benefits of treatment with your healthcare provider.

Nelarabine is a chemotherapy medication used in the treatment of T-cell acute lymphoblastic leukemia and T-cell lymphoblastic lymphoma. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. It is typically used when other treatments have not been successful. Like all chemotherapy drugs, nelarabine can have side effects, so it is important for patients to be closely monitored by their healthcare team while receiving this medication.

Neratinib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of breast cancer. It is a tyrosine kinase inhibitor, which works by blocking specific proteins that are involved in the growth and spread of cancer cells. Neratinib is typically prescribed for patients with early-stage HER2-positive breast cancer who have completed trastuzumab-based adjuvant therapy. It may also be used in other cases as determined by a healthcare provider. As with any medication, there may be side effects and interactions with other drugs, so it is important to follow your healthcare provider's guidance when taking Neratinib.

Nilotinib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, particularly chronic myeloid leukemia (CML). It belongs to a class of drugs known as tyrosine kinase inhibitors, which work by blocking the action of abnormal proteins that promote the growth of cancer cells. Nilotinib is usually taken orally in the form of a tablet and is prescribed by a healthcare provider. It is important to follow the prescribed dosage and instructions for taking this medication to ensure its effectiveness and reduce the risk of side effects. As with any medication, it is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of nilotinib with a healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Nilutamide is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as antiandrogens. It is used in the treatment of prostate cancer in combination with other medications. Nilutamide works by blocking the effects of male hormones like testosterone, which can help slow down the growth of prostate cancer cells. It is usually taken by mouth in the form of tablets. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and report any side effects or concerns while taking Nilutamide.

Nimustine is a chemotherapy drug used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as brain tumors and lymphomas. It belongs to a class of drugs known as alkylating agents, which work by interfering with the DNA of cancer cells, ultimately preventing their growth and spread. Nimustine is typically administered intravenously by a healthcare professional in a clinical setting. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions carefully when receiving this medication, as it can have side effects and may interact with other medications.

Nintedanib is a medication used to treat certain lung conditions such as idiopathic pulmonary fibrosis (IPF) and systemic sclerosis-associated interstitial lung disease (SSc-ILD). It works by targeting specific pathways in the body involved in the scarring of lung tissue. Nintedanib is usually taken in the form of oral capsules and is available by prescription only. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and discuss any potential side effects or concerns with them.

Niraparib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, specifically ovarian cancer. It belongs to a class of drugs known as PARP inhibitors, which work by blocking an enzyme involved in repairing damaged DNA in cancer cells. Niraparib is typically used in patients with recurrent ovarian cancer who have responded to platinum-based chemotherapy. It can help extend the time before the cancer progresses and may improve overall survival in some patients. As with any medication, it is important to consult with a healthcare provider for specific information and guidance on its use.

Nivolumab is a type of medication known as a checkpoint inhibitor, specifically a programmed cell death protein 1 (PD-1) inhibitor. It works by helping the immune system recognize and attack cancer cells. Nivolumab is used to treat various types of cancer, including melanoma, lung cancer, kidney cancer, and certain types of lymphoma. It is typically given as an intravenous infusion in a hospital or clinic setting. Like all medications, nivolumab can have side effects, so it is important to discuss the potential risks and benefits with a healthcare provider.

Non-pegylated liposomal doxorubicin is a type of chemotherapy medication used to treat various types of cancer, including ovarian cancer, breast cancer, and multiple myeloma. It is a formulation of the drug doxorubicin encapsulated within liposomes, which are tiny fat particles. This formulation helps to improve the delivery of the drug to the cancer cells and reduce its toxicity to normal cells. Non-pegylated liposomal doxorubicin may have fewer side effects compared to traditional doxorubicin but can still cause side effects such as nausea, vomiting, hair loss, and low blood cell counts. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of this medication with your healthcare provider.

Norethandrolone is a synthetic anabolic steroid that has been used in the past for various medical purposes, such as treating muscle wasting conditions. However, its use has declined over the years due to concerns about its potential side effects and the availability of safer alternatives. It is important to note that the use of anabolic steroids like norethandrolone without a prescription is illegal and can have serious health consequences. If you have any specific concerns or questions about norethandrolone, it would be best to consult with a healthcare professional.

Obinutuzumab is a type of monoclonal antibody used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, particularly non-Hodgkin's lymphoma. It works by targeting and binding to specific proteins on cancer cells, helping the immune system to recognize and destroy them. Obinutuzumab is often used in combination with other chemotherapy medications to improve treatment outcomes. Like any medication, it may have side effects, so it's important to discuss the potential risks and benefits with your healthcare provider.

Octreotide is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs called somatostatin analogs. It is used to treat conditions such as acromegaly (excess growth hormone production), carcinoid tumors, and vasoactive intestinal peptide-secreting tumors (VIPomas). Octreotide works by inhibiting the release of certain hormones in the body.

It is usually given by injection and may be administered either subcutaneously or intravenously. Common side effects of octreotide include nausea, diarrhea, abdominal pain, and headache. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when taking this medication.

Octreotide LAR is a long-acting formulation of the medication octreotide, which is a synthetic version of the hormone somatostatin. It is used to treat conditions such as acromegaly, carcinoid tumors, and certain symptoms of neuroendocrine tumors. The long-acting formulation allows for less frequent dosing compared to the immediate-release form of octreotide. It works by inhibiting the production and release of certain hormones in the body. As with any medication, it's important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and discuss any potential side effects or concerns.

Ofatumumab is a monoclonal antibody medication used to treat chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL) and relapsing forms of multiple sclerosis (MS). It works by targeting specific proteins on the surface of B cells, leading to their destruction. Ofatumumab is typically administered as an injection under the skin or into a vein by a healthcare provider. Like all medications, it can have potential side effects, so it's important to discuss with your healthcare provider if Ofatumumab is the right treatment for you.

Olaparib is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as PARP inhibitors. It is used in the treatment of certain types of ovarian, breast, and prostate cancers. Olaparib works by blocking the PARP enzyme, which helps to repair damaged DNA in cancer cells. By inhibiting this enzyme, olaparib can help prevent cancer cells from repairing themselves, leading to their death. It is typically used in patients with specific genetic mutations, such as BRCA mutations. As with any medication, olaparib may have side effects, so it is important to discuss the risks and benefits with your healthcare provider.

Olaratumab is a monoclonal antibody that targets platelet-derived growth factor receptor alpha (PDGFR-alpha). It is used in the treatment of certain types of soft tissue sarcoma in combination with chemotherapy. Olaratumab works by blocking the activity of PDGFR-alpha, which can help slow down the growth and spread of cancer cells. It is important to consult with a healthcare provider for more specific information about olaratumab and its use in your particular situation.

Omacetaxine is a prescription medication used to treat a type of leukemia called chronic myeloid leukemia (CML) that has not responded to other treatments or has relapsed. It works by blocking the growth of cancer cells. It is typically used when other treatments, such as tyrosine kinase inhibitors, have not been effective. Omacetaxine is usually given as an injection under the skin or into a vein by a healthcare provider. Like all medications, it can have side effects, so it is important to discuss the risks and benefits with your healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Omeprazole is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as proton pump inhibitors (PPIs). It is commonly used to treat conditions such as gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD), stomach ulcers, and conditions where the stomach produces too much acid. Omeprazole works by reducing the production of stomach acid, which can help relieve symptoms such as heartburn, acid reflux, and indigestion. It is usually taken orally in the form of a capsule or tablet. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and discuss any potential side effects or concerns.

Osimertinib is a medication used in the treatment of non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC) that has specific mutations in the epidermal growth factor receptor (EGFR) gene. It is known as a tyrosine kinase inhibitor, which works by blocking the activity of the EGFR protein to help slow or stop the growth of cancer cells. Osimertinib is typically prescribed for patients who have not responded to other EGFR inhibitors or whose cancer has progressed despite treatment with other medications. It is available in tablet form and is taken orally once daily. As with any medication, it is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks with your healthcare provider.

Oxaliplatin is a chemotherapy drug used to treat various types of cancer, including colorectal cancer. It works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells and is typically given intravenously in a clinical setting. Common side effects of oxaliplatin may include nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, numbness or tingling in the hands and feet, and changes in taste sensation. It is important to discuss any concerns or potential side effects with your healthcare provider before starting treatment with oxaliplatin.

Paclitaxel nanoparticle albumin-bound, also known by the brand name Abraxane, is a medication used in the treatment of various types of cancer, including breast cancer, lung cancer, and pancreatic cancer. It is a form of paclitaxel, a chemotherapy drug, that is bound to albumin nanoparticles to improve its delivery and effectiveness. This formulation helps to increase the concentration of paclitaxel in cancer cells while reducing side effects commonly associated with traditional paclitaxel. It is administered intravenously by a healthcare professional. Like all medications, Abraxane can have side effects, so it is important to discuss the risks and benefits with your healthcare provider.

Paclitaxel is a chemotherapy medication used to treat various types of cancer, including breast, ovarian, and lung cancer. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Paclitaxel is typically administered intravenously in a hospital or clinic setting. Common side effects may include hair loss, nausea, vomiting, and low blood cell counts. It is important to discuss any concerns or questions about Paclitaxel with a healthcare provider.

Pacritinib is a medication that is being studied for the treatment of certain types of blood disorders, including myelofibrosis and thrombocytopenia. It works by targeting specific enzymes involved in the regulation of blood cell production. Pacritinib is still under investigation in clinical trials to determine its safety and effectiveness, and it is not yet approved for widespread use. It's important to consult with a healthcare professional for the most up-to-date information on Pacritinib and its potential benefits and risks.

Palbociclib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of breast cancer. It is a targeted therapy that works by inhibiting specific proteins in cancer cells, slowing down their growth and division. Palbociclib is usually used in combination with other medications and is typically prescribed for hormone receptor-positive, HER2-negative breast cancer that has spread to other parts of the body. It is important to discuss with your healthcare provider for more information about Palbociclib, including its side effects and potential benefits for your specific situation.

Panitumumab is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, particularly colorectal cancer that has spread to other parts of the body. It is a targeted therapy that works by blocking the action of a protein called epidermal growth factor receptor (EGFR), which is involved in the growth and spread of cancer cells. Panitumumab is typically given by intravenous infusion and is prescribed by a healthcare provider. As with any medication, it may have side effects, so it's important to discuss with your healthcare team if panitumumab is the right treatment for you.

Panobinostat is a prescription medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as multiple myeloma. It belongs to a class of drugs known as histone deacetylase (HDAC) inhibitors, which work by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells. Panobinostat is typically used in combination with other cancer medications and is taken orally in capsule form. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions carefully when taking Panobinostat and to report any side effects or concerns promptly.

Pazopanib is a medication used to treat advanced renal cell carcinoma (kidney cancer), advanced soft tissue sarcoma, and advanced ovarian cancer. It belongs to a class of drugs known as tyrosine kinase inhibitors, which work by blocking the action of certain proteins that are involved in the growth and spread of cancer cells. It is usually taken orally in the form of tablets. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and discuss any potential side effects or concerns.

Pegaspargase is a medication used in the treatment of acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ALL), a type of blood cancer. It is a form of the enzyme L-asparaginase, which works by breaking down the amino acid asparagine, which is essential for the growth and survival of cancer cells. Pegaspargase is given as an injection and is often used in combination with other chemotherapy drugs to treat ALL. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when taking pegaspargase and to report any side effects you may experience.

Peginterferon alfa-2a is a medication used to treat chronic hepatitis B and C infections. It works by helping the immune system fight the virus and reduce inflammation in the liver. This medication is given by injection and is typically used in combination with other antiviral medications for the treatment of hepatitis. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions carefully when taking Peginterferon alfa-2a and to be aware of potential side effects.

Peginterferon alfa-2b is a medication used to treat certain viral infections, such as hepatitis B and hepatitis C. It belongs to a class of drugs known as interferons, which help the immune system fight off viruses. Peginterferon alfa-2b is given by injection under the skin and is typically used in combination with other medications for the treatment of hepatitis. As with any medication, it is important to discuss the potential risks and benefits with your healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Pegylated liposomal doxorubicin is a chemotherapy drug that is used to treat various types of cancer, including ovarian cancer, breast cancer, and multiple myeloma. It is a formulation of the drug doxorubicin encapsulated in liposomes and coated with polyethylene glycol (PEG) to help improve its circulation time in the body and reduce certain side effects. Pegylated liposomal doxorubicin is administered intravenously and works by targeting and killing cancer cells. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and side effects of this medication with your healthcare provider.

Pembrolizumab is a medication used in the treatment of various types of cancer, including melanoma, non-small cell lung cancer, head and neck squamous cell carcinoma, and others. Pemetrexed is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, including non-small cell lung cancer and mesothelioma. Pentostatin is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as antimetabolites. It is used to treat a type of blood cancer called hairy cell leukemia. Pertuzumab is a type of targeted therapy used in the treatment of HER2-positive breast cancer. Pirarubicin is a chemotherapy drug used to treat various types of cancer, including breast cancer, lung cancer, and bladder cancer. Pixantrone is a chemotherapy drug used to treat non-Hodgkin's lymphoma. Plicamycin, also known as Mithramycin, is a type of antibiotic medication that is used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, specifically testicular cancer and tumors of the bone. Pomalidomide is a medication used in the treatment of multiple myeloma, a type of cancer that affects plasma cells in the bone marrow. Pomalidomide is typically used in patients who have not responded to other treatments or have relapsed after previous therapies. Ponatinib is a medication used to treat certain types of leukemia, specifically chronic myeloid leukemia (CML) and acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ALL). Ponatinib is typically prescribed when other treatments have not been effective or if a specific genetic mutation is present. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions carefully when taking Ponatinib, as it can have side effects and interactions with other medications.

Pralatrexate is a chemotherapy drug used to treat a type of lymphoma called peripheral T-cell lymphoma. It works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells in the body. Pravastatin is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as statins. It is used to lower high levels of cholesterol and triglycerides in the blood. Pravastatin works by reducing the production of cholesterol in the liver and helping the body to remove it from the bloodstream. It is commonly prescribed to reduce the risk of heart attack, stroke, and other complications in patients with high cholesterol or other risk factors for heart disease.
