Prednisolone is a corticosteroid medication used to treat various conditions such as inflammation, allergies, autoimmune diseases, and certain types of cancer. Prednisone is a corticosteroid medication that is commonly used to treat a variety of conditions, including inflammatory disorders, autoimmune diseases, allergic reactions, and certain types of cancer. Procarbazine is a chemotherapy medication that is used to treat various types of cancer, including Hodgkin's disease and brain tumors. Quinine is a medication used to treat malaria. It works by killing the malaria parasites living inside red blood cells. Quizartinib is a medication used in the treatment of a type of blood cancer known as acute myeloid leukemia (AML). Radotinib is a medication used in the treatment of chronic myeloid leukemia (CML) that is resistant or intolerant to other tyrosine kinase inhibitors. Raltitrexed is a medication used in the treatment of advanced colorectal cancer. Raltitrexed is typically given by injection and is often used in combination with other chemotherapy drugs. Ramucirumab is a monoclonal antibody medication that is used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, including stomach cancer, gastroesophageal junction cancer, and non-small cell lung cancer. By inhibiting this protein, ramucirumab can help slow down or stop the growth of cancer cells. It is typically used in combination with other cancer treatments such as chemotherapy. Ranimustine, also known as nimustine, is a chemotherapy drug used to treat various types of cancer, including brain tumors and lymphomas. Regorafenib is a medication used to treat certain types of cancer, including colorectal cancer and liver cancer. Ribociclib is a medication used in the treatment of advanced or metastatic breast cancer in postmenopausal women. Ribociclib is typically used in combination with other medications and is taken orally as a tablet. Rituximab is a medication used to treat certain types of autoimmune diseases and cancers. It is a type of immunosuppressant that works by targeting and destroying specific cells in the immune system called B cells. Rituximab is a medication used to treat certain autoimmune diseases and types of cancer. Hyaluronidase human is an enzyme that helps to break down hyaluronic acid in the body, which can be useful in certain medical procedures and treatments. Romidepsin is a medication used in the treatment of a type of cancer called cutaneous T-cell lymphoma (CTCL). Ropeginterferon alfa-2b is a long-acting form of interferon alfa-2b that is used for the treatment of polycythemia vera, a type of blood cancer. Rucaparib is a medication used in the treatment of ovarian cancer. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and discuss any questions or concerns you may have.

Ruxolitinib is a medication used to treat certain types of myelofibrosis, a rare type of blood cancer. It is also used to treat polycythemia vera, a bone marrow disorder. Ruxolitinib works by blocking certain proteins in the body that are involved in the growth and spread of cancer cells. It is typically taken as a tablet by mouth. Sacituzumab govitecan is a type of cancer treatment known as an antibody-drug conjugate. It is used to treat certain types of cancer, including triple-negative breast cancer and metastatic urothelial cancer. Sargramostim is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as colony-stimulating factors. Selinexor is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as multiple myeloma and diffuse large B-cell lymphoma. It works by blocking the export of tumor-suppressive proteins from the cell nucleus, leading to the accumulation of these proteins in the nucleus and causing cancer cells to die. Selinexor is usually prescribed in combination with other cancer treatments. Like any medication, it may have side effects, so it's important to discuss with your healthcare provider if Selinexor is a suitable treatment option for you.

Selumetinib is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as MEK inhibitors. It is used in the treatment of certain types of cancers, such as melanoma and non-small cell lung cancer. It is typically used in combination with other cancer treatments and is only available with a prescription from a healthcare provider. Semustine is a chemotherapy drug used to treat certain types of cancer, such as brain tumors and lymphoma. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Sipuleucel-T is a personalized cancer immunotherapy used in the treatment of certain types of prostate cancer. Sonidegib is a prescription medication used to treat a type of skin cancer called basal cell carcinoma that has spread locally or cannot be treated with surgery or radiation therapy. Sorafenib is a medication used to treat liver cancer, kidney cancer, and thyroid cancer. It works by blocking certain proteins that help cancer cells grow and spread. Streptozocin is a chemotherapy medication that is used to treat certain types of cancer, including pancreatic islet cell cancer (a type of pancreatic cancer) and carcinoid tumors. Sunitinib is a medication used to treat certain types of cancer, including kidney cancer (renal cell carcinoma), gastrointestinal stromal tumors (GIST), and pancreatic neuroendocrine tumors. Tagraxofusp is a medication used for the treatment of blastic plasmacytoid dendritic cell neoplasm (BPDCN), a rare and aggressive type of blood cancer. Talazoparib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of breast cancer. Talimogene laherparepvec, also known as T-VEC, is a type of oncolytic virus therapy used in the treatment of melanoma, a type of skin cancer. Tamibarotene is a synthetic retinoid compound that is used as a treatment for a type of leukemia called acute promyelocytic leukemia (APL). It works by inducing leukemia cells to mature and die, thereby helping to reduce the number of abnormal cells in the body. Tamibarotene is often prescribed in combination with other chemotherapy agents for the treatment of APL. It is important to take tamibarotene exactly as prescribed by a healthcare provider and to follow their instructions carefully. Tamoxifen is a medication that is commonly used to treat breast cancer. Tamoxifen is also used to reduce the risk of breast cancer in women who are at high risk for the disease. Tegafur/gimeracil/oteracil, also known as S-1, is a combination drug used in the treatment of various types of cancers, including gastric cancer and colorectal cancer. Tegafur is a prodrug of 5-fluorouracil (5-FU), which is a chemotherapy medication. Gimeracil inhibits the breakdown of 5-FU, increasing its concentration in the body. Oteracil helps reduce the gastrointestinal side effects of 5-FU. This combination therapy is designed to enhance the effectiveness of 5-FU while minimizing its side effects. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of this medication with your healthcare provider.

Tegafur is a prodrug of 5-fluorouracil (5-FU), which is a chemotherapy medication used to treat various types of cancer, including breast, colon, and stomach cancers. Tegafur is converted into 5-FU in the body, where it exerts its anti-cancer effects by interfering with the growth of cancer cells.

Uracil is a naturally occurring nucleotide base that is a component of RNA molecules. When combined with Tegafur in a medication called Tegafur/uracil (UFT), it is used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, particularly colorectal cancer. The uracil component helps enhance the effectiveness of Tegafur by inhibiting the degradation of 5-FU in the body, leading to increased levels of the active drug in the cancer cells.

Temozolomide is a chemotherapy medication used to treat certain types of brain tumors, specifically glioblastoma multiforme and anaplastic astrocytoma. Teniposide is a chemotherapy medication used to treat various types of cancer, including leukemia and certain types of solid tumors. Thalidomide is a medication that was originally developed in the late 1950s as a sedative and anti-nausea drug. However, thalidomide gained notoriety for causing severe birth defects when taken by pregnant women, leading to thousands of babies being born with limb deformities. This tragic outcome led to stricter regulations on drug testing and approval processes to prevent similar incidents in the future.

Thioguanine is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as antimetabolites. Thiotepa is a type of chemotherapy drug used to treat various types of cancer, including breast, ovary, bladder, and lymphoma. It works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells in the body. Tisagenlecleucel, also known as Kymriah, is a type of chimeric antigen receptor (CAR) T-cell therapy used to treat certain types of cancer, particularly a form of leukemia called acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ALL) and certain types of lymphoma. Tivozanib is a medication used in the treatment of advanced renal cell carcinoma (kidney cancer). Tivozanib has been studied in clinical trials and has shown efficacy in certain patients with advanced kidney cancer. Topotecan is a prescription medication used to treat certain types of cancer, including ovarian cancer, small cell lung cancer, and cervical cancer. Toremifene is a medication that is used in the treatment of advanced breast cancer in postmenopausal women. Trabectedin is a type of chemotherapy drug used to treat certain types of cancer, such as soft tissue sarcoma and ovarian cancer. Trametinib is a medication used to treat certain types of cancer, specifically melanoma with a specific mutation. It works by blocking certain proteins in cancer cells that help them grow and spread. Tranexamic acid is a medication that is used to prevent or reduce bleeding. It works by helping to slow down the breakdown of blood clots in the body. Treosulfan is a chemotherapy drug used to treat certain types of cancer, such as ovarian cancer and bone marrow disorders. Trifluridine and tipiracil is a combination medication used to treat certain types of cancer, specifically metastatic colorectal cancer and metastatic gastric or gastroesophageal junction adenocarcinoma. Triptorelin is a synthetic hormone used in the treatment of certain medical conditions, such as prostate cancer, breast cancer, and endometriosis. Valproate is a medication that is commonly used to treat epilepsy, bipolar disorder, and migraines. Valrubicin is a medication used to treat bladder cancer. It belongs to a class of drugs called anthracyclines, which work by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Vandetanib is a medication that is used to treat a type of thyroid cancer called medullary thyroid cancer. It works by blocking certain proteins that help cancer cells grow and spread. Vemurafenib is a prescription medication used to treat a type of skin cancer called melanoma that has a specific genetic mutation known as BRAF V600E. Vemurafenib is usually taken orally in the form of tablets and is typically prescribed by oncologists or dermatologists. Venetoclax is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of leukemia, specifically chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL) and small lymphocytic lymphoma (SLL). Like all medications, Crizotinib can have side effects and interactions with other drugs, so it is important to take it under the supervision of a healthcare provider.

Cyclophosphamide is a medication used in the treatment of various types of cancer, including leukemia, lymphoma, and multiple myeloma. It belongs to a class of drugs known as alkylating agents, which work by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Cyclophosphamide is often used in combination with other chemotherapy drugs and is typically administered intravenously. It can also be used to treat certain autoimmune diseases, such as lupus and rheumatoid arthritis. However, it can have side effects, including nausea, vomiting, hair loss, and increased risk of infections. It is important to discuss the risks and benefits of cyclophosphamide treatment with your healthcare provider.

Cyproterone acetate is a medication that is used for a variety of purposes, including the treatment of prostate cancer, hirsutism (excessive hair growth), acne, androgenetic alopecia (male pattern baldness), and in hormone replacement therapy for transgender women. It is also commonly used as a component of some oral contraceptives. However, it is important to note that Cyproterone acetate can have potential side effects and may not be suitable for everyone, so it is best to discuss its use with a healthcare provider.

Cytarabine is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, including leukemia. It is a type of chemotherapy drug that works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Cytarabine is often given by injection into a vein or under the skin. It can have side effects such as nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, and lowered blood cell counts. It is important to follow your doctor's instructions carefully while taking Cytarabine.

Cytarabine and daunorubicin liposomal is a combination chemotherapy treatment used to treat certain types of leukemia, such as acute myeloid leukemia (AML). It consists of two medications, cytarabine (also known as cytosine arabinoside) and daunorubicin, encapsulated in liposomes to help deliver the drugs directly to cancer cells.

Cytarabine works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells, while daunorubicin is a type of anthracycline chemotherapy that also helps to kill cancer cells. By combining these drugs in liposomes, it may enhance their effectiveness in targeting and killing cancer cells while reducing some side effects.

As with any cancer treatment, there may be side effects associated with cytarabine and daunorubicin liposomal, and it is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks with a medical professional.

Dabrafenib is a medication used to treat certain types of skin cancer, such as melanoma, that have specific genetic mutations. It belongs to a class of drugs known as kinase inhibitors, which work by blocking abnormal proteins that promote the growth of cancer cells. Dabrafenib is typically used in combination with other medications for maximum effectiveness. As with any medication, it is important to follow your doctor's instructions and report any side effects.

Dacarbazine is a type of chemotherapy medication used to treat various types of cancer, including melanoma, Hodgkin's lymphoma, and soft tissue sarcomas. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Common side effects of Dacarbazine may include nausea, vomiting, loss of appetite, and temporary hair loss. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of Dacarbazine with a healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Dacomitinib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of lung cancer. It belongs to a class of drugs known as tyrosine kinase inhibitors, which work by blocking specific proteins that help cancer cells grow and spread. Dacomitinib is typically prescribed for patients with non-small cell lung cancer that has certain genetic mutations. Like all medications, Dacomitinib can have side effects, so it is important to discuss with your healthcare provider if it is the right treatment option for you.

Dactinomycin is a type of chemotherapy medication that is used to treat various types of cancer, including Wilms' tumor, rhabdomyosarcoma, Ewing's sarcoma, and gestational trophoblastic neoplasia. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Dactinomycin is usually given as an injection into a vein by a healthcare provider. Like all chemotherapy medications, dactinomycin may cause side effects, so it is important to discuss the potential risks and benefits with your healthcare provider.

Danazol is a synthetic androgen (male hormone) that is used in the treatment of various medical conditions. It is primarily used to treat endometriosis, a condition in which tissue similar to the lining of the uterus grows outside of the uterus. Danazol can help reduce pain, infertility, and other symptoms associated with endometriosis. It is also used to treat hereditary angioedema, a rare genetic disorder that causes episodes of swelling in various parts of the body. Danazol works by suppressing the production of certain hormones in the body. It is available in oral capsule form and should be taken exactly as prescribed by a healthcare provider. Like any medication, Danazol can cause side effects, so it is important to discuss any concerns with a healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Daratumumab is a monoclonal antibody that is used in the treatment of multiple myeloma, a type of cancer that affects plasma cells in the bone marrow. It works by targeting a specific protein on the surface of myeloma cells, which helps the immune system to identify and attack these cancer cells. Daratumumab can be used alone or in combination with other medications to treat multiple myeloma in certain patients. It is important to discuss with your healthcare provider about the potential benefits and risks of daratumumab in your specific situation.

Darolutamide is a medication used for the treatment of prostate cancer. It belongs to a class of drugs known as androgen receptor inhibitors. Darolutamide works by blocking the effects of androgens (male hormones) on prostate cancer cells, thereby slowing down the growth and spread of cancer. It is typically used in combination with other treatments for advanced prostate cancer. As with any medication, it is important to consult with a healthcare provider for more information and guidance on its use.

Dasatinib is a medication typically used to treat certain types of leukemia, such as chronic myeloid leukemia (CML) and acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ALL). It belongs to a class of medications called tyrosine kinase inhibitors, which work by blocking certain proteins that help cancer cells grow and divide. Dasatinib is usually taken as a pill by mouth and is often prescribed by oncologists or hematologists. As with any medication, it is important to follow your doctor's instructions carefully and discuss any potential side effects or concerns with them.

Daunorubicin is a type of chemotherapy drug that is used to treat certain types of cancer, such as leukemia and lymphoma. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Daunorubicin is typically given as an infusion into a vein by a healthcare provider. Like all chemotherapy drugs, daunorubicin can have side effects, so it is important to discuss with your healthcare provider any concerns or questions you may have about this medication.

Daunorubicin liposomal is a medication used to treat certain types of cancer, including leukemia. It is a type of chemotherapy drug that works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. The liposomal formulation helps to increase the delivery of the drug to the cancer cells while reducing some of the side effects commonly associated with traditional Daunorubicin. It is important to follow your doctor's instructions carefully when taking this medication and to be aware of potential side effects.

Decitabine is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as myelodysplastic syndromes (MDS). It works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells in the body. Decitabine is a type of chemotherapy drug and is usually given by injection into a vein. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions carefully when receiving treatment with Decitabine. Like all medications, Decitabine can have side effects, so it's essential to discuss any concerns with your healthcare team.

Degarelix is a medication used for the treatment of advanced prostate cancer. It works by decreasing the production of certain hormones that can stimulate the growth of prostate cancer cells. Degarelix is typically administered as an injection under the skin by a healthcare provider. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when taking Degarelix and to discuss any potential side effects or concerns with them.

Denileukin diftitox is a medication used in the treatment of cutaneous T-cell lymphoma (CTCL), a type of skin cancer. It is a fusion protein that combines interleukin-2 (IL-2) and diphtheria toxin. The IL-2 component targets and binds to specific receptors on cancerous T-cells, while the diphtheria toxin component enters the cells and inhibits protein synthesis, leading to cell death. Denileukin diftitox is administered through intravenous infusion and is usually reserved for patients who have not responded to other treatments. As with any medication, it may have side effects, so it is important to discuss with your healthcare provider about the potential benefits and risks of using denileukin diftitox.

Denosumab is a medication used to treat osteoporosis and bone-related conditions. It works by increasing bone density and reducing the risk of fractures. Denosumab is usually administered as an injection under the skin and is typically given every 6 months. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when taking denosumab to ensure its effectiveness and minimize potential side effects.

Dexamethasone is a type of corticosteroid medication commonly used to reduce inflammation in the body. It is often prescribed to treat conditions such as allergies, skin conditions, asthma, arthritis, and certain types of cancer. In recent times, it has gained attention for its potential effectiveness in reducing inflammation and improving outcomes in severe cases of COVID-19. However, like all medications, dexamethasone can have side effects and should be taken only under the supervision of a healthcare professional.

Dexrazoxane is a medication that is used to help prevent or reduce heart damage in patients receiving certain types of chemotherapy treatments, such as doxorubicin or epirubicin, which can be toxic to the heart. Dexrazoxane works by protecting the heart cells from the damage caused by these chemotherapy drugs. It is typically administered before each dose of chemotherapy to help minimize the risk of heart-related side effects. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's recommendations and discuss any concerns about this medication with them.

Diethylstilbestrol (DES) is a synthetic form of the hormone estrogen. It was prescribed to pregnant women between the 1940s and 1970s to prevent miscarriages and other pregnancy complications. However, it was later discovered that DES exposure during pregnancy can lead to serious health problems in both the mothers and their children, such as an increased risk of certain cancers and reproductive issues. DES is no longer used in pregnancy due to these risks.

Dinutuximab is a therapeutic antibody used in the treatment of high-risk neuroblastoma, a type of cancer that mainly affects children. It works by targeting and binding to a specific protein found on neuroblastoma cells, helping the immune system to identify and destroy the cancer cells. Dinutuximab is typically used in combination with other treatments, such as chemotherapy and surgery, to improve outcomes for patients with high-risk neuroblastoma. As with any medication, there may be potential side effects and risks associated with dinutuximab, so it is important to discuss with a healthcare provider for more information.

Docetaxel is a type of chemotherapy medication used to treat various types of cancer, including breast cancer, lung cancer, and prostate cancer. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Docetaxel is usually given through a vein by injection and is often used in combination with other chemotherapy drugs. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's recommendations and monitor for any potential side effects while receiving docetaxel treatment.

Doxifluridine is a chemotherapy drug that is used to treat certain types of cancer, including stomach cancer. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. It is important to follow your doctor's instructions when taking this medication, as it can have side effects and interactions with other drugs. If you have any questions or concerns about Doxifluridine, it is best to consult with your healthcare provider.

Doxorubicin is a chemotherapy medication that is used to treat various types of cancer, including breast cancer, lung cancer, and leukemia. It works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells and is often administered intravenously by a healthcare provider. It can cause side effects such as nausea, vomiting, hair loss, and increased risk of infections. It is important to discuss any concerns or questions about Doxorubicin with a healthcare provider.

Durvalumab is a type of monoclonal antibody used in cancer treatment. It is classified as an immune checkpoint inhibitor and works by blocking a protein called PD-L1 on cancer cells, which allows the immune system to better recognize and attack the cancer cells. Durvalumab is approved for the treatment of certain types of cancer, including non-small cell lung cancer and bladder cancer. It is typically used in combination with other cancer treatments. It is important to discuss with a healthcare provider for more specific information about Durvalumab and its use in treating cancer.

Dutasteride is a medication used to treat symptoms of an enlarged prostate, a condition also known as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH). It belongs to a class of drugs called 5-alpha-reductase inhibitors, which work by decreasing the production of dihydrotestosterone (DHT) in the body. Dutasteride helps to reduce the size of the prostate gland and improve urinary symptoms associated with BPH. It is available in oral capsule form and should be taken as prescribed by a healthcare provider. As with any medication, there may be side effects or interactions, so it's important to discuss with a doctor before starting Dutasteride.

Duvelisib is a medication used to treat certain types of blood cancers, such as chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL) and small lymphocytic lymphoma (SLL). It belongs to a class of drugs known as PI3K inhibitors, which work by blocking a specific enzyme involved in the growth and spread of cancer cells. It is typically used in patients who have not responded to other treatments or who have relapsed after initial therapy. As with any medication, there are potential side effects and interactions to be aware of, so it's important to talk to your healthcare provider for personalized information.

Edrecolomab is a monoclonal antibody that was developed as a potential treatment for certain types of cancer, particularly colorectal cancer. It works by targeting a specific protein found on the surface of cancer cells. However, clinical trials for Edrecolomab did not show significant benefits, and it is no longer widely used in cancer treatment. It's always best to consult with a healthcare professional for the most up-to-date information on cancer treatments.

Elotuzumab is a monoclonal antibody medication used for the treatment of multiple myeloma, a type of cancer that affects plasma cells in the bone marrow. It works by targeting a specific protein on the surface of myeloma cells called SLAMF7, which helps the immune system to recognize and attack the cancer cells. Elotuzumab is often used in combination with other medications for the treatment of multiple myeloma. Like all medications, it may have side effects, so it is important to discuss with your healthcare provider before starting treatment with Elotuzumab.

Enasidenib is a medication used in the treatment of a specific type of blood cancer called acute myeloid leukemia (AML). It works by targeting a specific mutation in the IDH2 gene, which helps to slow down the growth of cancer cells. Enasidenib is typically used in patients who have relapsed or refractory AML and have been previously treated with other medications. It is important to discuss with your healthcare provider about the potential benefits and risks of taking Enasidenib.

Encorafenib is a prescription medication used to treat certain types of skin cancer, specifically melanoma. It belongs to a class of medications known as BRAF inhibitors, which work by blocking the activity of a specific gene mutation that is commonly found in melanoma cells. Encorafenib is typically used in combination with other medications, such as binimetinib, for the treatment of melanoma that cannot be surgically removed or that has spread to other parts of the body. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and discuss any questions or concerns you may have.

Entrectinib is a prescription medication used to treat certain types of cancer, such as non-small cell lung cancer, solid tumors, and specific types of genetic abnormalities. It acts as a tyrosine kinase inhibitor, working to block specific proteins involved in the growth and spread of cancer cells. It's important to consult with a healthcare provider for personalized information and guidance on the use of Entrectinib.

Enzalutamide is a prescription medication used to treat prostate cancer. It belongs to a class of medications known as anti-androgens, and works by blocking the effects of androgens (male hormones) on the cancer cells. Enzalutamide is typically prescribed for men with advanced prostate cancer that has spread to other parts of the body and is no longer responding to other treatments. It is important to take Enzalutamide exactly as prescribed by your doctor and to discuss any potential side effects or concerns with your healthcare provider.

Epirubicin is a chemotherapy drug that is used to treat various types of cancer, including breast cancer, ovarian cancer, and stomach cancer. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Epirubicin is typically administered intravenously by a healthcare provider and can have side effects such as nausea, vomiting, hair loss, and decreased blood cell counts. Erdafitinib is a prescription medicine used to treat a certain type of bladder cancer that has spread or cannot be removed by surgery. It belongs to a class of medications called FGFR inhibitors, which work by blocking certain proteins involved in the growth and spread of cancer cells. It is important to talk to your healthcare provider about the potential benefits and risks of Erdafitinib treatment.

Eribulin is a chemotherapy medication used to treat certain types of cancer, including metastatic breast cancer and liposarcoma. It works by disrupting the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Eribulin is usually given as an intravenous injection by a healthcare provider. Like all medications, Eribulin can have side effects, so it's important to discuss potential risks and benefits with your healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Erlotinib is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as tyrosine kinase inhibitors. It is used in the treatment of non-small cell lung cancer and pancreatic cancer. Erlotinib works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells, particularly by blocking a protein called epidermal growth factor receptor (EGFR) that is involved in the growth and spread of cancer cells. It is usually taken by mouth in the form of a tablet. As with any medication, Erlotinib can have side effects and may not be suitable for everyone, so it's essential to consult with a healthcare provider before taking it.

Estramustine is a medication used in the treatment of advanced prostate cancer. It is a combination of estradiol, a form of the hormone estrogen, and nitrogen mustard, a type of chemotherapy drug. Estramustine works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells. It is typically given orally in the form of capsules. As with any medication, it is important to follow the instructions of your healthcare provider when taking Estramustine and to be aware of potential side effects and interactions with other medications.

Etoposide is a medication commonly used in cancer treatment, particularly for lung cancer, testicular cancer, and certain types of leukemia and lymphoma. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Etoposide is usually given by injection or infusion in a hospital setting under the supervision of a healthcare provider. Like all medications, etoposide can have side effects, including nausea, vomiting, hair loss, and a decreased number of white blood cells. It's important to discuss any concerns or questions about etoposide with a healthcare professional.

Everolimus is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs called mTOR inhibitors. It is used to treat various types of cancer, including advanced kidney cancer, breast cancer, and certain types of neuroendocrine tumors. Everolimus works by inhibiting the mTOR protein, which plays a crucial role in cell growth and division. This helps slow down or stop the growth of cancer cells. It is typically taken orally in the form of tablets. Like all medications, Everolimus has potential side effects, so it is important to discuss with your healthcare provider if it is the right treatment option for you.

Exemestane is a medication used to treat breast cancer in postmenopausal women. It belongs to a class of drugs known as aromatase inhibitors, which work by reducing the amount of estrogen produced in the body. This can help slow or stop the growth of hormone receptor-positive breast cancer cells. Exemestane is typically taken orally once a day and may be prescribed as part of a treatment plan for breast cancer following surgery or other treatments. Like all medications, Exemestane can have side effects, so it's important to discuss any concerns with your healthcare provider.

Floxuridine is a chemotherapy medication used in the treatment of various types of cancer, including colorectal cancer. It works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells, ultimately helping to slow down or stop the spread of cancer in the body. Floxuridine is typically administered intravenously under the supervision of a healthcare provider. Like all chemotherapy drugs, Floxuridine can cause side effects, which can vary from person to person. Fludarabine is a chemotherapy drug used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as leukemia and lymphoma. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Fludarabine is usually given as an injection or infusion in a hospital or clinic setting. Common side effects may include nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, and lowered blood cell counts. It is important to talk to your healthcare provider about the potential benefits and risks of treatment with Fludarabine.

Fluorouracil is a chemotherapy medication used to treat various types of cancer, including breast, colon, skin, and stomach cancers. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Fluorouracil is usually given as an infusion into a vein or as a topical cream for certain skin conditions. Like all chemotherapy drugs, Fluorouracil can cause side effects, such as nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, and low blood cell counts. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of Fluorouracil treatment with your healthcare provider.

Fluoxymesterone, marketed under the brand name Halotestin, is a synthetic derivative of testosterone. It is classified as an anabolic steroid and is commonly used to treat low testosterone levels in men. Fluoxymesterone is also used to improve strength and athletic performance, particularly in power sports such as weightlifting and bodybuilding. However, it is important to note that the use of fluoxymesterone for non-medical purposes can have serious side effects and should only be used under medical supervision.

Flutamide is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as antiandrogens. It is mainly used in the treatment of prostate cancer and hirsutism (excessive hair growth). Flutamide works by blocking the action of androgens (male hormones) in the body, which can help slow down the growth of cancer cells in prostate cancer and reduce the growth of unwanted hair in hirsutism. It is usually taken in combination with other medications for better effectiveness. Flutamide may have some side effects, so it is important to take it as prescribed by a healthcare professional and discuss any concerns with your doctor.

Folinic acid, also known as leucovorin, is a form of folate that is used as a nutritional supplement and in medicine. It is often prescribed to help treat certain types of anemia, to counteract the toxic effects of some medications, and to enhance the efficacy of certain cancer treatments. Folinic acid is also sometimes used in the treatment of conditions like methotrexate toxicity and megaloblastic anemia. It is available by prescription and should be taken under the supervision of a healthcare provider.

Formestane is a synthetic compound also known as 4-hydroxyandrostenedione. It is classified as an aromatase inhibitor, which means it can reduce the production of estrogen in the body by blocking aromatase enzymes. This reduction in estrogen levels can be beneficial for athletes and bodybuilders looking to control estrogen-related side effects, such as water retention and gynecomastia, while on a steroid cycle. Formestane has also been used in the treatment of estrogen-receptor-positive breast cancer. As with any compound, it is important to use Formestane responsibly and follow proper dosing guidelines to minimize potential side effects.

Forodesine is a drug that belongs to a class of medications known as purine nucleoside phosphorylase inhibitors. It is being investigated for its potential use in the treatment of certain types of cancer and autoimmune diseases. Clinical trials are ongoing to evaluate its safety and effectiveness in these conditions. However, it is important to consult with a healthcare professional for the most up-to-date and accurate information on Forodesine.

Fostamatinib is a prescription medication that is used to treat adults with chronic immune thrombocytopenia (ITP), a condition characterized by low levels of platelets in the blood. It works by helping the body to produce more platelets, which are necessary for proper blood clotting. Fostamatinib is typically taken as a tablet by mouth, and it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when taking this medication. It is important to note that Fostamatinib may have side effects and interactions with other medications, so it is essential to discuss these with your healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Fotemustine is a chemotherapy drug used to treat certain types of brain tumors, such as melanoma metastases. It works by damaging the DNA of cancer cells, which helps to slow down or stop their growth. Fotemustine is usually given intravenously under the supervision of a healthcare provider. Like any medication, Fotemustine can cause side effects, so it's important to discuss the potential risks and benefits with your doctor before starting treatment.

Fulvestrant is a medication used in the treatment of hormone receptor-positive breast cancer in postmenopausal women. It belongs to a class of drugs known as selective estrogen receptor degraders (SERDs). Fulvestrant works by binding to estrogen receptors in the body and blocking the effects of estrogen, which can inhibit the growth of hormone-sensitive breast cancer cells. It is usually given as an injection and is prescribed by healthcare providers in specific treatment regimens based on individual patient needs. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when taking Fulvestrant and to discuss any questions or concerns you may have with them.

Gefitinib is a medication used in the treatment of non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC) that has certain mutations. It belongs to a class of medications called tyrosine kinase inhibitors, which work by blocking specific proteins in cancer cells to help slow down or stop their growth. Gefitinib is typically taken orally in tablet form, and it is important to follow the prescribed dosage and directions provided by your healthcare provider. Like any medication, Gefitinib may have potential side effects, so it's essential to discuss these with your doctor before starting treatment.

Gemcitabine is a chemotherapy medication used to treat various types of cancer, including pancreatic, lung, breast, and bladder cancer. It is usually given by injection into a vein. Gemcitabine works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells and slowing down their spread in the body. Common side effects of gemcitabine may include nausea, vomiting, fatigue, low blood cell counts, and hair loss. It is important to discuss any concerns or potential side effects with your healthcare provider.

Gemtuzumab ozogamicin is a medication used for the treatment of acute myeloid leukemia (AML). It is a targeted therapy that works by attaching to a protein on the surface of leukemia cells and delivering a toxic substance directly to the cancer cells, which helps to destroy them. Gemtuzumab ozogamicin is typically used in combination with chemotherapy for certain patients with AML. It is important to note that this medication can have side effects, so it should only be used under the supervision of a healthcare provider experienced in its use.

Gilteritinib is a medication used in the treatment of acute myeloid leukemia (AML). It is an inhibitor of the FLT3 gene mutation, which is commonly found in AML patients. Gilteritinib works by targeting and blocking the mutated FLT3 protein, which can help slow down the growth and spread of leukemia cells. This medication is usually prescribed for patients with relapsed or refractory AML. It is important to consult with a healthcare provider for more information on using Gilteritinib and its potential side effects.

Glasdegib is a medication used to treat newly diagnosed acute myeloid leukemia (AML) in adult patients who are not eligible for intensive chemotherapy. It works by inhibiting a protein called Smoothened, which is involved in the abnormal development of cancer cells. It is usually taken in combination with other chemotherapy drugs. Like all medications, Glasdegib may have side effects, so it's important to discuss with your healthcare provider before starting this treatment.

Goserelin is a synthetic hormone used in the treatment of certain medical conditions, such as prostate cancer, breast cancer, and endometriosis. It works by decreasing the production of certain hormones in the body. Goserelin is typically given as an injection and should only be used under the supervision of a healthcare provider. It is important to follow the dosage and administration instructions provided by your healthcare provider to ensure safe and effective treatment. Like all medications, Goserelin may have side effects, so it is important to discuss any concerns with your healthcare provider.

Histrelin is a medication used to treat symptoms of advanced prostate cancer and central precocious puberty. It is a synthetic form of a hormone that works by reducing the production of certain hormones in the body. Histrelin is usually administered as an implant placed under the skin, where it slowly releases the medication over a period of several months. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when using Histrelin and to discuss any potential side effects or concerns with them.

Hydrocortisone is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as corticosteroids. It is commonly used to reduce inflammation and itching associated with various skin conditions such as eczema, rashes, and dermatitis. Hydrocortisone works by decreasing the body's immune response to reduce symptoms like redness, swelling, and itching. It is available in various forms including creams, ointments, lotions, and sprays, and is typically applied topically to the affected area of the skin. It is important to use hydrocortisone as directed by a healthcare professional to avoid potential side effects and to achieve the best results.

Hydroxyurea is a medication that is used for the treatment of various conditions, including sickle cell anemia, certain types of cancer (such as leukemia and melanoma), and polycythemia vera. It works by slowing down the production of red blood cells, which can be beneficial in certain conditions. It is important to take Hydroxyurea exactly as prescribed by a healthcare provider and to follow their instructions closely. Like all medications, Hydroxyurea can have side effects, so it is important to discuss any concerns with a healthcare provider.

Ibritumomab tiuxetan is a type of cancer treatment known as radioimmunotherapy. It is used in the treatment of certain types of non-Hodgkin's lymphoma. The medication consists of a monoclonal antibody that targets a specific protein on cancer cells, which is linked to a radioactive substance that helps to kill the cancer cells. Ibritumomab tiuxetan is administered intravenously and works by delivering radiation directly to the cancer cells while minimizing exposure to healthy tissues. It is typically used when other treatments have not been effective or as a consolidation therapy after initial treatment. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of ibritumomab tiuxetan with a healthcare provider.

Ibrutinib is a medication used to treat certain types of cancer such as chronic lymphocytic leukemia, mantle cell lymphoma, and Waldenstrom's macroglobulinemia. It works by blocking certain proteins in the body that help cancer cells grow and spread. It is usually taken orally and can have various side effects, so it's important to discuss with a healthcare provider before starting this medication.

Icotinib is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as tyrosine kinase inhibitors. It is used in the treatment of non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC) that has metastasized or progressed after other treatments. Icotinib works by blocking the activity of a specific protein called epidermal growth factor receptor (EGFR), which plays a role in the growth and spread of cancer cells. It is typically taken orally in tablet form. As with any medication, it is important to follow the prescribed dosage and consult with a healthcare provider for more information and possible side effects.

Idarubicin is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, including leukemia. It belongs to a class of drugs known as anthracyclines, which work by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Idarubicin is typically given by injection into a vein by a healthcare provider in a hospital setting. It is important to discuss any questions or concerns about Idarubicin with your healthcare provider.

Idelalisib is a medication that is used in the treatment of certain types of blood cancers, such as chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL) and non-Hodgkin lymphoma. It works by targeting specific proteins in the cancer cells, which helps to slow down the growth of the cancer. Idelalisib is typically used in combination with other cancer treatments and is available in oral tablet form. As with any medication, it is important to talk to your doctor about the potential benefits and side effects of Idelalisib before starting treatment.

Ifosfamide is a type of chemotherapy medication used to treat various types of cancer, including testicular, ovarian, and lung cancers. It is important to discuss the potential risks and benefits of ifosfamide treatment with your healthcare provider.

Imatinib is a medication used to treat certain types of cancers, such as chronic myeloid leukemia (CML), gastrointestinal stromal tumors (GISTs), and other conditions related to abnormal cell growth. It works by targeting specific proteins that are involved in the growth and spread of cancer cells. Imatinib is usually taken by mouth in tablet form and is often well-tolerated by patients, but like any medication, it can have side effects that should be discussed with a healthcare provider. It has been a key drug in the treatment of CML and has significantly improved the prognosis for patients with this type of cancer.

Infigratinib is a drug that belongs to a class of medications known as fibroblast growth factor receptor (FGFR) inhibitors. It is used for the treatment of certain types of cancers, such as cholangiocarcinoma (bile duct cancer) and urothelial carcinoma (bladder cancer), that have specific genetic mutations. Infigratinib works by targeting and inhibiting the FGFR proteins that are involved in the growth and spread of cancer cells. It is typically used when other treatments have not been successful or are no longer effective. It is important to discuss with your doctor about the potential benefits and risks of using Infigratinib for your specific condition.

Sure! Inotuzumab ozogamicin is a type of targeted therapy used in the treatment of certain types of leukemia, specifically acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ALL). It is an antibody-drug conjugate that works by attaching to a protein on leukemia cells and delivering a toxic substance directly to the cancer cells, which can help to slow down or stop their growth. It is typically used when other treatments have not been effective. As with any medication, it can have side effects, so it's important to discuss the risks and benefits with a healthcare provider.

Interferon alfa-2a is a medication used to treat certain types of cancers, such as hairy cell leukemia, melanoma, and AIDS-related Kaposi's sarcoma. It is a type of protein called a cytokine that helps the immune system fight off infections and potentially slow down the growth of cancer cells. Interferon alfa-2a is typically given as an injection under the skin or into a muscle. Like all medications, it can have side effects, so it's important to discuss them with your healthcare provider.

Interferon alfa-2b is a medication classified as an immunomodulator that helps the body fight against viruses and cancer cells. It is used to treat various conditions such as chronic hepatitis B and C, certain types of cancer (like melanoma and leukemia), and certain viral infections. Interferon alfa-2b works by boosting the body's immune response to help fight off these diseases. It is typically administered by injection and may have side effects such as flu-like symptoms, fatigue, and decreased blood cell counts.

Interferon gamma-1b is a medication used to treat chronic granulomatous disease and severe, malignant osteopetrosis. It works by increasing the immune system's response to infections and tumors. It is a synthetic version of a naturally occurring protein in the body called interferon gamma. As with any medication, it is important to follow the instructions of your healthcare provider when using interferon gamma-1b.

Ipilimumab is a monoclonal antibody medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as melanoma and kidney cancer. It works by activating the body's immune system to attack cancer cells. Ipilimumab is sometimes used in combination with other cancer treatments. Like any medication, it may have side effects, so it is important to discuss the risks and benefits with a healthcare provider.

Irinotecan is a type of chemotherapy medication used to treat various types of cancer, including colorectal cancer. It works by interfering with the way cancer cells grow and spread, ultimately helping to slow or stop the growth of cancer cells. Irinotecan is typically given through intravenous infusion in a clinical setting and can cause side effects such as diarrhea, nausea, and hair loss. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of irinotecan treatment with your healthcare provider.

Irinotecan liposome, also known as Onivyde, is a medication used to treat pancreatic cancer. It is a type of chemotherapy drug that works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Irinotecan liposome is typically given through intravenous infusion and is used in combination with other medications for the treatment of advanced pancreatic cancer that has spread to other parts of the body. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and side effects of Irinotecan liposome with your healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Isatuximab is a monoclonal antibody used in the treatment of multiple myeloma, a type of cancer that affects plasma cells in the bone marrow. It works by targeting a protein called CD38, which is found on the surface of myeloma cells, leading to their destruction. Isatuximab is typically used in combination with other medications for the treatment of relapsed or refractory multiple myeloma. As with any medication, it is important to consult with a healthcare provider for more information about Isatuximab, including its potential side effects and effectiveness.

Isotretinoin is a prescription medication used to treat severe acne that has not responded to other treatments. It is a form of vitamin A and works by reducing the amount of oil produced by the skin's oil glands. Isotretinoin is known to be highly effective in treating severe acne, but it can also have some potentially serious side effects, so it is important to take it under the supervision of a healthcare provider. It is also known by the brand names Accutane, Absorica, and others.

Ivosidenib is a medication used to treat acute myeloid leukemia (AML), a type of cancer that affects the bone marrow and blood. It works by targeting specific genetic mutations that drive the growth of cancer cells. Ivosidenib is often prescribed for patients with AML who have a specific genetic mutation called IDH1. It is available in oral form and is typically taken once daily. Like all medications, Ivosidenib can have side effects, so it's important to discuss with your healthcare provider if it is the right treatment for you.

Ixabepilone is a chemotherapy medication used in the treatment of various types of cancer, such as breast cancer and lung cancer. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. It is typically given intravenously by a healthcare provider. As with any medication, it may cause side effects, so it's important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and discuss any concerns with them.

Ixazomib is a medication used in the treatment of multiple myeloma, a type of cancer that affects plasma cells in the bone marrow. It is a proteasome inhibitor, which means it works by blocking the action of proteasomes, enzymes that break down proteins in cells. By inhibiting proteasomes, ixazomib can help stop the growth and spread of cancer cells. It is often used in combination with other medications to treat multiple myeloma. As with any medication, it is important to discuss with your healthcare provider about the potential benefits and risks of ixazomib treatment.

Ketoconazole is an antifungal medication used to treat a variety of fungal infections. It works by inhibiting the growth of fungi. Ketoconazole can be used topically to treat skin infections like athlete's foot or orally to treat systemic fungal infections. It is important to follow the instructions of a healthcare provider when using this medication due to potential side effects and drug interactions.

Lanreotide is a medication used to treat certain types of tumors such as neuroendocrine tumors and acromegaly. It works by binding to specific receptors in the body to help control hormone levels that may be elevated due to these conditions. Lanreotide is usually administered as an injection and can help improve symptoms and slow down the growth of tumors in some cases. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when taking Lanreotide and to discuss any potential side effects or concerns with them.

Lansoprazole is a proton pump inhibitor (PPI) that is commonly used to treat conditions such as gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD), ulcers, and other conditions caused by excess stomach acid. It works by reducing the amount of acid the stomach produces, helping to alleviate symptoms such as heartburn and indigestion. It is available as a prescription medication and over-the-counter in some countries. It's important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when taking Lansoprazole to ensure safe and effective treatment.

Lapatinib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of breast cancer. It is a type of targeted therapy that works by blocking specific proteins that are involved in the growth of cancer cells. Lapatinib is typically used in combination with other cancer treatments and is prescribed by a healthcare provider. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and discuss any questions or concerns you may have about Lapatinib treatment.

Larotrectinib, marketed under the brand name Vitrakvi, is a medication used to treat certain types of cancer, specifically solid tumors that have a specific genetic alteration called an NTRK gene fusion. This targeted therapy works by inhibiting proteins produced by the NTRK genes, which can help to slow or stop the growth of cancer cells. It has shown promising results in clinical trials for patients with NTRK fusion-positive tumors. Like all medications, it is important to speak with a healthcare provider to determine if Larotrectinib is the right treatment option for a particular individual.

Lenalidomide is a prescription medication used to treat certain types of cancer, including multiple myeloma and myelodysplastic syndromes. It works by helping the immune system slow down the growth of cancer cells and reduce inflammation in the body. Like any medication, lenalidomide may cause side effects, so it's important to discuss any concerns with a healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Lenograstim is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as granulocyte colony-stimulating factors (G-CSF). It is used to stimulate the production of white blood cells in the bone marrow, particularly neutrophils, which are important for fighting infections. Lenograstim is commonly used in cancer patients undergoing chemotherapy to prevent or treat low white blood cell counts, which can increase the risk of infection. It may also be prescribed for other conditions where a boost in white blood cell production is needed. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when taking Lenograstim.

Lenvatinib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as thyroid cancer and liver cancer. It works by slowing down or stopping the growth of cancer cells. Lenvatinib is usually taken in the form of a pill and is prescribed by a healthcare provider. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and report any side effects you may experience while taking this medication.

Letrozole is a medication that is commonly used to treat breast cancer in postmenopausal women. It belongs to a class of drugs known as aromatase inhibitors, which work by reducing the production of estrogen in the body. By lowering estrogen levels, Letrozole can help slow or stop the growth of certain types of breast cancer that rely on estrogen to grow. It is typically taken in the form of a daily oral tablet. Letrozole is also sometimes used off-label to help stimulate ovulation in women who are struggling with infertility. It is important to take Letrozole exactly as prescribed by a doctor and to discuss any potential side effects or concerns with a healthcare provider.

Leuprolide is a medication used in the treatment of certain hormone-related conditions such as prostate cancer, endometriosis, and certain types of breast cancer. It belongs to a class of drugs known as gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH) agonists, which work by decreasing the production of certain hormones in the body. It is typically administered by injection and is available under various brand names. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and discuss any potential side effects or concerns with them.

Levamisole is a medication that was initially used as an anthelminthic to treat parasitic worm infections. It has also been used in the past as an immunomodulator to boost the immune system. However, its use has declined due to potential serious side effects, including skin conditions, blood disorders, and, in some cases, an increased risk of developing serious infections. Levamisole is not recommended for routine use without medical supervision.

Levoleucovorin, also known as L-leucovorin or calcium folinate, is a medication used in combination with other chemotherapy drugs to treat certain types of cancer. It is a form of folic acid that helps protect healthy cells from the effects of chemotherapy while enhancing the effectiveness of the cancer treatment. Levoleucovorin is typically administered by a healthcare professional and is available in injectable form. As with any medication, it is important to follow the prescribed dosage and advice of your healthcare provider.

Lomustine, also known as CCNU, is a chemotherapy medication used to treat certain types of cancer, such as brain tumors, Hodgkin's disease, and certain types of lymphoma. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Lomustine is usually taken as a capsule by mouth. It may have serious side effects, so it is important to follow the prescribed dosage and monitoring plan closely while taking this medication. It is always best to consult with a healthcare provider for more detailed information about Lomustine and its potential benefits and risks for your specific situation.

Lorlatinib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of advanced non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC). It is a type of targeted therapy known as a tyrosine kinase inhibitor, which works by blocking specific proteins in cancer cells that help them grow and spread. Lorlatinib is typically prescribed for patients who have specific genetic mutations in their cancer cells, such as ALK or ROS1 gene rearrangements. It is taken orally in the form of tablets and is usually prescribed by a healthcare provider specializing in cancer treatment. Like all medications, lorlatinib can have side effects, so it's important for patients to discuss the potential risks and benefits with their healthcare team.

Lutetium Lu 177 dotatate is a radiopharmaceutical used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, specifically neuroendocrine tumors. It works by targeting cancer cells that have a specific receptor for somatostatin, a hormone involved in the regulation of various bodily functions. The Lutetium Lu 177 isotope emits beta particles that deliver radiation directly to the cancer cells, helping to destroy them. This treatment is typically used for patients who have failed other therapies or have tumors that have spread to other parts of the body. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of this treatment with a healthcare provider.

Tafasitamab is a type of cancer treatment known as a monoclonal antibody. It is used for the treatment of certain types of non-Hodgkin lymphoma, specifically diffuse large B-cell lymphoma that has not responded to other treatments or has relapsed. Tafasitamab works by targeting and binding to specific proteins on cancer cells, which can help the immune system identify and destroy the cancer cells. It is typically used in combination with other cancer treatments. As with any medication, it is important to discuss the potential risks and benefits with your healthcare provider.

Mechlorethamine, also known as mustine, is a chemotherapy medication used to treat certain types of cancer, including Hodgkin's disease, non-Hodgkin's lymphoma, and skin cancer. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Mechlorethamine is usually given by injection into a vein or applied topically to the skin in the form of a cream or gel. Like all chemotherapy drugs, Mechlorethamine can cause side effects, including nausea, vomiting, decreased blood cell counts, and increased risk of infections. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions carefully while taking Mechlorethamine and to report any side effects promptly.

Medroxyprogesterone is a medication that is used for various purposes, including treating irregular menstrual periods, endometriosis, and abnormal uterine bleeding. It is also used as a form of birth control and in hormone replacement therapy. Medroxyprogesterone is a synthetic form of the hormone progesterone and works by affecting the lining of the uterus. It is available in different forms such as tablets, injections, and implants, and should be used under the guidance of a healthcare provider. It is important to discuss any potential side effects and risks of using medroxyprogesterone with a healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Megestrol is a synthetic progestin medication that is used for various purposes, including treating breast cancer, endometrial cancer, and loss of appetite and weight loss in patients with HIV/AIDS. It is also sometimes used off-label to treat certain hormonal conditions. Megestrol works by mimicking the effects of the hormone progesterone in the body. It is available in various forms, including tablets and oral suspension. As with any medication, it is important to take Megestrol as prescribed by a healthcare provider and to discuss any potential side effects or concerns with them.

Melphalan is a type of chemotherapy medication that is used to treat certain types of cancer, including multiple myeloma and ovarian cancer. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Melphalan is usually given by injection or taken orally in the form of a tablet. Like all chemotherapy drugs, Melphalan can have side effects, including nausea, vomiting, hair loss, and decreased blood cell counts. It is important to talk to your healthcare provider about the risks and benefits of treatment with Melphalan.

Mercaptopurine is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as antimetabolites. It is commonly used to treat certain types of cancer, such as acute lymphoblastic leukemia, as well as certain autoimmune conditions like inflammatory bowel disease. Mercaptopurine works by interfering with the growth of abnormal cells in the body.

It is important to take Mercaptopurine exactly as prescribed by your healthcare provider and to follow their instructions carefully. This medication may have potential side effects, so it is essential to discuss any concerns or questions with your healthcare provider.

As with any medication, it is important to inform your healthcare provider about any other medications or supplements you are taking to avoid potential interactions.

Mesna is a medication that is used to prevent or reduce the side effects of certain chemotherapy drugs, particularly ifosfamide and cyclophosphamide. It works by binding to toxic metabolites produced by these drugs, preventing them from causing damage to the bladder and kidney. Mesna is often given intravenously or orally, and it is generally well-tolerated with few side effects. It is an important supportive therapy in cancer treatment to help minimize the harmful effects of certain chemotherapy drugs.

Methotrexate is a prescription medication that is used to treat certain types of cancer, rheumatoid arthritis, psoriasis, and other autoimmune conditions. It works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells and suppressing the immune system to reduce inflammation. Methotrexate is taken either orally or by injection, and it is important to closely follow your healthcare provider's instructions while taking this medication due to potential side effects and interactions with other medications. Common side effects may include nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, and liver toxicity. It is important to discuss any concerns or questions you have about Methotrexate with your healthcare provider.

Methoxsalen is a medication used to treat severe psoriasis and certain skin conditions by increasing the skin's sensitivity to light, making it easier to treat with ultraviolet light therapy. It is also sometimes used in combination with UVA light therapy for the treatment of vitiligo. Methoxsalen works by making the skin more sensitive to ultraviolet light, which can help slow down the growth of skin cells and improve various skin conditions. It is important to use this medication exactly as directed by your healthcare provider to minimize the risk of side effects. If you have any questions or concerns about Methoxsalen, it's best to consult with your healthcare provider.

Methylprednisolone is a corticosteroid medication used to reduce inflammation and suppress the immune system. It is commonly prescribed to treat conditions such as allergic reactions, asthma, arthritis, skin conditions, and certain types of cancer. It can be taken orally or given through an injection, and should only be used under the guidance of a healthcare provider due to potential side effects and interactions with other medications. It is important to follow the prescribed dosage and duration of treatment to minimize the risk of adverse effects.

Midostaurin is a medication that is used to treat certain types of leukemia, specifically acute myeloid leukemia (AML) and advanced systemic mastocytosis. It works by inhibiting certain proteins in the body that are involved in the growth and spread of cancer cells. Midostaurin is typically taken in the form of capsules and is usually prescribed by a doctor specializing in the treatment of leukemia. It is important to follow your doctor's instructions carefully while taking this medication and to report any side effects or concerns promptly.

Mitomycin is a type of chemotherapy medication often used to treat various types of cancer, including stomach, pancreatic, bladder, and lung cancers. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Mitomycin is typically administered by injection into a vein or directly into the cancerous area. As with any chemotherapy drug, Mitomycin can have side effects, such as nausea, vomiting, fatigue, and lowered blood cell counts. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of Mitomycin treatment with a healthcare provider.

Mitotane, also known by the brand name Lysodren, is a medication commonly used in the treatment of adrenal cortical carcinoma, a type of cancer that affects the adrenal glands. Mitotane works by disrupting the function of the adrenal glands, which can help reduce the production of certain hormones that may fuel the growth of cancer cells. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions carefully when taking Mitotane, as it can have significant side effects and may require close monitoring. Be sure to discuss any questions or concerns with your doctor or pharmacist.

Mitoxantrone is a type of chemotherapy medication that is used to treat certain types of cancer, such as leukemia, lymphoma, and breast cancer. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Mitoxantrone is often given by injection into a vein and is typically administered in a hospital or clinic setting. It can have side effects, including nausea, hair loss, weakness, and increased risk of infection. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of Mitoxantrone with your healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Mogamulizumab is a monoclonal antibody used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as cutaneous T-cell lymphoma (CTCL) and adult T-cell leukemia-lymphoma (ATLL). It works by targeting a specific protein on the surface of cancer cells, leading to their destruction by the immune system. Mogamulizumab is typically administered by intravenous infusion and may have side effects such as infusion reactions, skin rashes, and infections. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of mogamulizumab with a healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Moxetumomab pasudotox is a medication used for the treatment of hairy cell leukemia (HCL). It is a type of immunotoxin, which means it combines a targeting agent (an antibody) with a toxin to specifically target and kill cancer cells. Moxetumomab pasudotox targets a protein called CD22, which is found on the surface of HCL cells. By binding to CD22, the medication delivers a toxin directly to the cancer cells, causing them to die. It is typically used in patients who have not responded to or have relapsed after other treatments for HCL. As with any medication, it is important to discuss the potential benefits and side effects with your healthcare provider.

Nadroparin is a type of medication known as a low molecular weight heparin. It is used to prevent blood clots in conditions such as deep vein thrombosis, pulmonary embolism, and during certain medical procedures or surgeries. Nadroparin works by inhibiting clot formation in the blood vessels. It is usually administered by injection under the skin. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and report any side effects or concerns.

Necitumumab is a medication used to treat certain types of advanced non-small cell lung cancer. It is a monoclonal antibody that works by targeting a protein on cancer cells called EGFR, which can help slow down the growth and spread of cancer cells. It is typically used in combination with other cancer medications. Like all medications, it may have side effects, so it's important to discuss the risks and benefits with your healthcare provider.

Nedaplatin is a chemotherapy drug used to treat various types of cancer, including lung, bladder, and cervical cancer. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Nedaplatin is typically given by injection into a vein and is used in combination with other cancer medications. Like all chemotherapy drugs, Nedaplatin can have side effects, including nausea, vomiting, hair loss, and low blood cell counts. It is important to discuss the potential risks and benefits of Nedaplatin with a healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Nelarabine is a chemotherapy medication used to treat certain types of leukemia, specifically T-cell acute lymphoblastic leukemia (T-ALL) and T-cell lymphoblastic lymphoma (T-LBL). It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Nelarabine is usually given intravenously by a healthcare provider in a hospital or clinic setting. Like all chemotherapy drugs, nelarabine can have side effects, so it is important to discuss potential risks and benefits with your healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Neratinib is a drug used in the treatment of breast cancer. It belongs to a class of medications called kinase inhibitors, which work by blocking certain proteins that promote the growth of cancer cells. Neratinib is typically used in patients with HER2-positive breast cancer, either alone or in combination with other drugs. It is available in tablet form and is prescribed by healthcare providers for specific cases of breast cancer. Like all medications, neratinib can have side effects, so it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and report any unusual symptoms while taking this medication.

Nilotinib is a prescription medication used to treat certain types of blood cancers, specifically chronic myeloid leukemia (CML). It belongs to a class of drugs called tyrosine kinase inhibitors, which work by blocking the action of an abnormal protein that promotes the growth of cancer cells. Nilotinib is typically taken orally in the form of capsules or tablets, and it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions carefully when taking this medication. Like all medications, nilotinib can have side effects, so it's important to discuss any potential risks with your doctor before starting treatment.

Nilutamide is a medication used in the treatment of prostate cancer. It belongs to a class of drugs known as antiandrogens, which work by blocking the effects of male hormones like testosterone on prostate cancer cells. Nilutamide is typically used in combination with other medications or treatments for advanced prostate cancer. Common side effects may include hot flashes, decreased libido, and liver function abnormalities. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when taking Nilutamide and report any concerning side effects.

Nimustine, also known as ACNU, is a chemotherapy drug used in the treatment of various types of cancer, including brain tumors and glioblastoma multiforme. It belongs to a class of drugs called alkylating agents, which work by interfering with the DNA of cancer cells, preventing them from growing and multiplying. Nimustine is usually administered intravenously or taken orally, and it can have side effects such as nausea, vomiting, hair loss, and lowered blood cell counts. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of Nimustine with a healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Nintedanib is a medication used in the treatment of certain lung diseases such as idiopathic pulmonary fibrosis (IPF) and systemic sclerosis-associated interstitial lung disease (SSc-ILD). It works by targeting and blocking certain pathways involved in the development of fibrosis in the lungs. Nintedanib is typically taken orally in the form of a capsule or tablet, and it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when taking this medication. Like all medications, Nintedanib can have side effects, so it's essential to discuss any concerns with your healthcare provider.

Niraparib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, specifically ovarian cancer and certain types of advanced cancer of the female reproductive system. It belongs to a class of drugs called PARP inhibitors, which work by interfering with the ability of cancer cells to repair damage to their DNA. Niraparib is typically used after other treatments have been tried and may help to slow down or stop the growth of cancer cells. It is important to talk to a healthcare provider for more information on Niraparib, its uses, side effects, and potential benefits.

Nivolumab is a type of immunotherapy medication used to treat certain types of cancer. It works by targeting a protein called PD-1 on immune cells, which helps the body's immune system to attack and destroy cancer cells. Nivolumab has been approved for the treatment of various cancers, including melanoma, lung cancer, kidney cancer, and more. It is typically given as an infusion in a medical setting. As with any medication, there can be side effects, so it's important to discuss with your healthcare provider if Nivolumab is a suitable treatment option for you.

Non-pegylated liposomal doxorubicin is a formulation of the chemotherapy drug doxorubicin encapsulated in liposomes, which are tiny fat particles.
