These liposomes help deliver the drug to the tumor site more effectively and reduce its toxicity to healthy tissues. Non-pegylated means that these liposomes do not have polyethylene glycol (PEG) molecules attached to their surface. This formulation is used in the treatment of various types of cancers, such as breast cancer, ovarian cancer, and Kaposi sarcoma. It can help improve the therapeutic efficacy and reduce side effects compared to conventional doxorubicin. Your healthcare provider can provide more information about this treatment option if it is appropriate for your condition.

Norethandrolone is a synthetic anabolic steroid that has been used in the treatment of certain medical conditions, such as muscle-wasting diseases. It is known for its ability to increase muscle mass and strength. However, it is important to note that the use of anabolic steroids like norethandrolone can have serious side effects and should only be used under the supervision of a healthcare professional.

Obinutuzumab is a type of biologic therapy known as a monoclonal antibody. It is used in the treatment of certain types of blood cancers, such as chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL) and certain types of non-Hodgkin lymphoma. Obinutuzumab works by targeting specific proteins on the surface of cancer cells, helping the immune system to recognize and destroy these cells. It is typically administered as an intravenous infusion in a healthcare setting. As with any medication, it can have potential side effects, so it's important to discuss any concerns with your healthcare provider.

Octreotide is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs called somatostatin analogues. It is used to treat a variety of conditions, including acromegaly, a condition in which the body produces too much growth hormone; carcinoid tumors, a type of cancer that can cause hormone imbalances; and symptoms of severe diarrhea and flushing in patients with certain types of tumors. Octreotide works by inhibiting the release of certain hormones in the body. It is available in injectable form for use in hospitals or clinics. It is important to use Octreotide under the guidance and supervision of a healthcare professional.

Octreotide LAR is a long-acting formulation of the medication octreotide, which is a synthetic version of the hormone somatostatin. It is used to treat certain hormone-secreting tumors in the gastrointestinal tract and pancreas, such as carcinoid tumors and acromegaly. Octreotide LAR works by reducing the production and release of various hormones in the body, helping to control symptoms and slow down the growth of tumors. It is usually administered by injection once every 4 weeks. Common side effects may include injection site reactions, gastrointestinal disturbances, and changes in blood sugar levels. It's important to follow your doctor's instructions carefully while taking Octreotide LAR.

Ofatumumab is a monoclonal antibody medication that is used to treat certain types of blood cancers, such as chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL) and certain types of non-Hodgkin's lymphoma. It works by targeting a specific protein on the surface of cancer cells, which helps the immune system to recognize and attack these cells. Ofatumumab is typically given as an infusion in a healthcare setting. It is important to discuss any questions or concerns you have about this medication with your healthcare provider.

Olaparib is a medication used in oncology for the treatment of certain types of cancer, particularly ovarian and breast cancer. It belongs to a class of drugs known as PARP inhibitors, which work by preventing cancer cells from repairing their DNA, ultimately leading to cell death. Olaparib is often used in patients with specific genetic mutations, such as BRCA mutations, to target cancer cells more effectively. It is available in tablet form and is typically prescribed by oncologists as part of a comprehensive treatment plan for cancer patients. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's guidance and discuss any questions or concerns you may have about Olaparib.

Olaratumab is a monoclonal antibody drug that is used in combination with chemotherapy to treat certain types of soft tissue sarcoma in adults. It works by targeting a protein called platelet-derived growth factor receptor alpha (PDGFR-alpha) to slow down the growth of cancer cells. This medication should be used under the supervision of a healthcare provider experienced in cancer treatment. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of Olaratumab with your healthcare provider.

Omacetaxine is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of leukemia. It works by inhibiting protein synthesis in cancer cells, ultimately leading to their death. Omacetaxine is typically used when other treatments have not been effective or have stopped working. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and be aware of potential side effects.

Omeprazole is a medication used to reduce the production of stomach acid. It belongs to a class of drugs known as proton pump inhibitors (PPIs). Omeprazole is commonly prescribed to treat conditions such as gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD), ulcers, and conditions where excessive stomach acid causes discomfort. It is usually taken by mouth in the form of capsules or tablets, and it is generally well-tolerated. However, like any medication, it can have side effects and interactions with other drugs, so it's important to use it under the guidance of a healthcare provider.

Osimertinib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC). It is a targeted therapy that works by blocking the activity of a specific protein called epidermal growth factor receptor (EGFR), which is involved in the growth and spread of cancer cells. Osimertinib is typically prescribed for patients whose cancer has specific mutations in the EGFR gene. It is available in tablet form and is taken orally once a day. Like all medications, Osimertinib may cause side effects, so it's important to discuss any concerns with your healthcare provider.

Oxaliplatin is a chemotherapy medication used to treat colon or rectal cancer. It is a platinum-based drug that works by inhibiting the growth of cancer cells. Side effects can include nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, nerve damage, and low blood cell counts. It is typically given intravenously in a hospital or clinic setting. It is important to discuss with your doctor about the potential benefits and risks of Oxaliplatin treatment.

Paclitaxel nanoparticle albumin-bound, also known as nab-paclitaxel, is a medication used in the treatment of various types of cancer, including breast cancer, pancreatic cancer, and lung cancer. It is a form of paclitaxel, a chemotherapy drug, that is bound to albumin nanoparticles to improve its delivery and effectiveness. Nab-paclitaxel works by disrupting the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. It is administered intravenously by a healthcare professional and may have fewer side effects compared to traditional paclitaxel formulations. It is important to consult with your healthcare provider for more information on this medication and its potential benefits and side effects.

Paclitaxel is a chemotherapy medication used to treat various types of cancer, including breast, lung, and ovarian cancer. It works by interfering with the ability of cancer cells to divide and grow. Common side effects of paclitaxel include hair loss, fatigue, numbness or tingling in the hands and feet, and low blood cell counts. It is usually given intravenously by a healthcare provider in a hospital or clinic setting. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when undergoing treatment with paclitaxel.

Pacritinib is a medication that is being developed for the treatment of certain types of cancers, including myelofibrosis and acute myeloid leukemia. It works by targeting specific receptors in the body that are involved in the growth and spread of cancer cells. Pacritinib is still under clinical investigation, and its safety and effectiveness are being studied in clinical trials. It is important to consult with a healthcare professional for accurate and up-to-date information on this medication.

Palbociclib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of breast cancer. It belongs to a class of drugs known as CDK 4/6 inhibitors, which work by blocking proteins that promote the growth of cancer cells. Palbociclib is often used in combination with other cancer medications and is typically prescribed by oncologists for specific types of breast cancer that are hormone receptor-positive and HER2-negative. As with any medication, there may be side effects and it is important to discuss any concerns with your healthcare provider.

Panitumumab is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, specifically metastatic colorectal cancer. It belongs to a class of medications known as monoclonal antibodies, which work by targeting and inhibiting the activity of certain proteins involved in the growth and spread of cancer cells. It is typically used in combination with other chemotherapy medications and is administered intravenously. As with any medication, Panitumumab may have side effects and should only be used under the supervision of a healthcare provider.

Panobinostat is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancers, such as multiple myeloma. It belongs to a class of drugs known as histone deacetylase inhibitors, which work by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells. Panobinostat is usually taken in combination with other cancer medications and is available in the form of tablets. As with any cancer treatment, it is important to discuss the potential benefits and side effects of panobinostat with a healthcare provider.

Pazopanib is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs called tyrosine kinase inhibitors, which are used in cancer treatment. It is commonly prescribed for the treatment of certain types of advanced kidney cancer (renal cell carcinoma) and soft tissue sarcomas. Pazopanib works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells and reducing the blood supply to the tumor. It is important to take this medication exactly as prescribed by your doctor and to discuss any potential side effects with your healthcare provider.

Pegaspargase is a medication used in the treatment of acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ALL), a type of cancer affecting the white blood cells. It is a form of the enzyme L-asparaginase that works by breaking down the amino acid asparagine, which cancer cells depend on for growth and survival. Pegaspargase is administered by injection and is often given in combination with other chemotherapy medications as part of a treatment regimen for ALL. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions carefully when taking Pegaspargase and to watch for any potential side effects.

Peginterferon alfa-2a is a medication used to treat certain viral infections, such as hepatitis B and hepatitis C. It works by helping the immune system fight the virus and reduce inflammation in the body. Peginterferon alfa-2a is usually given as an injection under the skin and should be used under the supervision of a healthcare provider. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and discuss any potential side effects or concerns with them.

Peginterferon alfa-2b is a medication used to treat certain viral infections, including hepatitis B and C. It belongs to a class of drugs called interferons, which help the immune system fight off viruses. Peginterferon alfa-2b is typically given as an injection under the skin and is often used in combination with other medications to increase effectiveness. Like any medication, it can have side effects, so it's important to discuss risks and benefits with a healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Pegylated liposomal doxorubicin is a chemotherapy drug used to treat various types of cancer, such as ovarian cancer, breast cancer, and multiple myeloma. It is a formulation of doxorubicin, a potent anti-cancer drug, encapsulated in liposomes (tiny fat particles) and modified with polyethylene glycol (PEG) to increase its circulation time in the body. This formulation helps reduce the side effects commonly associated with conventional doxorubicin, such as heart damage and tissue toxicity. Pegylated liposomal doxorubicin is administered intravenously and works by targeting and destroying cancer cells while minimizing damage to healthy tissues. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when receiving this medication and to be aware of potential side effects.

Pembrolizumab is a medication used in the treatment of various types of cancers, including melanoma, non-small cell lung cancer, head and neck cancer, and Hodgkin lymphoma. It belongs to a class of drugs known as immune checkpoint inhibitors, which work by helping the immune system recognize and attack cancer cells. Pembrolizumab is given as an intravenous infusion and is typically used in combination with other cancer treatments. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of pembrolizumab with a healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Pemetrexed is a chemotherapy drug used to treat certain types of cancer, including non-small cell lung cancer and mesothelioma. It works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells and is usually given in combination with other medications. Common side effects may include fatigue, nausea, vomiting, and decreased blood cell counts. It is important to follow your doctor's instructions and report any side effects during treatment.

Pentostatin is a medication used to treat hairy cell leukemia, a rare type of blood cancer. It works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells in the body. Pentostatin is usually given as an injection into a vein by a healthcare provider in a hospital or clinic setting. It may have side effects such as nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, and low blood cell counts. It's important to discuss the risks and benefits of Pentostatin treatment with your healthcare provider.

Pertuzumab is a monoclonal antibody medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as metastatic breast cancer. It works by targeting a specific protein that promotes the growth of cancer cells. Pertuzumab is often used in combination with other cancer medications to improve treatment outcomes. Like all medications, Pertuzumab may cause side effects, so it's important to discuss the risks and benefits with a healthcare provider.

Pirarubicin is a chemotherapy drug that belongs to the anthracycline class of medications. It is used to treat various types of cancer, including breast cancer, bladder cancer, and lung cancer. Pirarubicin works by interfering with the DNA of cancer cells, preventing them from growing and dividing. Like other chemotherapy drugs, Pirarubicin can cause side effects such as nausea, vomiting, hair loss, and low blood cell counts. It is important to discuss the potential risks and benefits of Pirarubicin treatment with a healthcare provider.

Pixantrone is a chemotherapy medication used to treat non-Hodgkin's lymphoma, a type of cancer that affects the lymphatic system. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. It is typically used in patients whose cancer has not responded to other treatments or has relapsed. Like all medications, it can have side effects and should be used under the supervision of a healthcare provider.

Plicamycin, also known as mithramycin, is a medication that belongs to a group of antibiotics called aureolic acid derivatives. It is primarily used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as testicular cancer, Ewing's sarcoma, and hypercalcemia (high levels of calcium in the blood) associated with cancer. Plicamycin works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. It is usually administered intravenously by a healthcare professional. It is important to note that plicamycin can have serious side effects and should only be used under the supervision of a qualified healthcare provider.

Pomalidomide is a medication used in the treatment of multiple myeloma, a type of cancer that affects the plasma cells in the bone marrow. It belongs to a class of drugs known as immunomodulatory agents and works by helping the immune system to attack and destroy cancer cells. It is typically used in patients who have not responded well to other treatments. As with any medication, it is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks with your healthcare provider before starting treatment with Pomalidomide.

Ponatinib is a prescription medication used to treat certain types of leukemia, specifically chronic myeloid leukemia (CML) and acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ALL). It belongs to a class of medications called tyrosine kinase inhibitors, which work by blocking certain proteins that help cancer cells grow and divide. Ponatinib is typically used when other treatments have not been effective or if the leukemia has a specific genetic mutation called the T315I mutation. It is important to take Ponatinib exactly as prescribed by a healthcare provider and to report any side effects or concerns while taking the medication.

Pralatrexate is a chemotherapy drug used to treat certain types of cancer, including peripheral T-cell lymphoma. It works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells and is typically given by injection into a vein. Like all chemotherapy drugs, Pralatrexate can cause side effects, which may include decreased blood cell counts, nausea, vomiting, fatigue, and mouth sores. It is important for patients to discuss the potential benefits and risks of Pralatrexate with their healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Pravastatin is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as statins. It is commonly used to lower cholesterol levels in the blood, thereby reducing the risk of heart disease. Pravastatin works by inhibiting the enzyme HMG-CoA reductase, which plays a key role in the production of cholesterol in the liver. It is typically prescribed in combination with a healthy diet and exercise to effectively manage cholesterol levels. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and closely monitor for any potential side effects.

Prednisolone is a corticosteroid medication that is used to reduce inflammation and suppress the immune system. It is commonly prescribed to treat a variety of conditions such as allergies, asthma, arthritis, and certain skin disorders. Prednisolone can have side effects, so it's important to take it exactly as prescribed by your doctor and to discuss any concerns with them.

Prednisone is a type of corticosteroid medication that is commonly used to treat inflammation, allergies, autoimmune disorders, and certain types of cancer. It works by suppressing the immune system and reducing inflammation in the body. Prednisone can be taken orally in tablet form or as an injection. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when taking prednisone, as it can have side effects and may interact with other medications. It is typically prescribed for short-term use due to the potential for side effects with long-term use. Be sure to discuss any concerns or questions you have with your healthcare provider.

Procarbazine is a chemotherapy medication used to treat various types of cancer, including Hodgkin's disease, certain brain tumors, and other types of cancer. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Procarbazine is often used in combination with other chemotherapy drugs to increase effectiveness. However, it can have serious side effects, so it is important to take this medication as directed by a healthcare professional.

Quinine is a natural compound extracted from the bark of the cinchona tree. It has been used historically to treat malaria due to its anti-parasitic properties. Quinine is also known for its bitter taste and is sometimes used in small amounts to flavor drinks like tonic water. However, it is important to note that the use of quinine for malaria treatment is not as common today due to the development of more effective and less toxic medications.

Quizartinib is a drug that belongs to a class of medications known as tyrosine kinase inhibitors. It is used in the treatment of a certain type of acute myeloid leukemia (AML) called FLT3-ITD positive AML. Quizartinib works by targeting and inhibiting specific enzymes that are involved in the growth and spread of cancer cells. It is typically used in patients who have relapsed or refractory AML, meaning the cancer has come back or has not responded to other treatments. Like any medication, Quizartinib can have side effects, so it is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks with a healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Radotinib is a tyrosine kinase inhibitor used to treat chronic myeloid leukemia (CML). It works by blocking certain proteins that promote the growth of cancer cells. Radotinib is typically prescribed when other treatments have not been effective or have caused intolerable side effects. As with any medication, it is important to follow your doctor's instructions and guidance while taking Radotinib.

Raltitrexed is a chemotherapy medication used in the treatment of various types of cancer, including colorectal cancer. It works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells and is typically used in combination with other chemotherapy drugs. Common side effects of raltitrexed may include nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, and decreased blood cell counts. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of raltitrexed with your healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Ramucirumab is a monoclonal antibody drug that is used to treat certain types of cancer, including stomach cancer, colorectal cancer, and non-small cell lung cancer. It works by targeting and blocking a protein called vascular endothelial growth factor receptor 2 (VEGFR2), which can help to slow down or stop the growth of blood vessels that supply tumors with nutrients and oxygen. Ramucirumab is typically given as an intravenous infusion in a hospital or clinic setting under the supervision of healthcare professionals. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when receiving this medication and to discuss any potential side effects or concerns with them.

Ranimustine is a chemotherapy drug that is used to treat certain types of cancer, such as lymphoma and brain tumors. It works by slowing or stopping the growth of cancer cells in the body. Like all chemotherapy drugs, Ranimustine may have some side effects, including nausea, hair loss, and increased risk of infection. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of Ranimustine with your healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Regorafenib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as colorectal cancer and gastrointestinal stromal tumors. It belongs to a class of drugs known as multi-kinase inhibitors, which work by blocking specific enzymes that help cancer cells grow and spread. Regorafenib is typically used when other treatments have not been effective or for advanced stages of cancer. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and discuss any potential side effects or concerns.

Ribociclib is a medication used to treat certain types of breast cancer. It belongs to a class of drugs known as CDK4/6 inhibitors, which work by helping to slow or stop the growth of cancer cells. Ribociclib is usually taken in combination with other medications and is prescribed by a doctor for specific types of breast cancer that are hormone receptor-positive and HER2-negative. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when taking Ribociclib and to be aware of any potential side effects.

Rituximab is a medication commonly used to treat certain autoimmune diseases, such as rheumatoid arthritis, lupus, and specific types of cancer, like non-Hodgkin's lymphoma and chronic lymphocytic leukemia. It works by targeting a specific protein on the surface of certain immune cells, leading to their destruction. Rituximab is usually given intravenously in a healthcare setting and may be accompanied by potential side effects like infusion reactions, infections, and lowered blood cell counts. It's important to discuss the benefits and risks of rituximab with a healthcare provider if considering this treatment.

Rituximab and hyaluronidase human is a combination medication used in the treatment of certain blood cancers such as Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma and chronic lymphocytic leukemia. Rituximab is a monoclonal antibody that works by targeting specific proteins on cancer cells and helping the immune system to attack and destroy them. Hyaluronidase human is an enzyme that helps rituximab to be absorbed more quickly into the body when injected under the skin. This combination treatment is administered as an injection under the skin and is typically given by a healthcare professional in a medical setting. Please consult with your doctor for more information on this medication and its potential side effects.

Romidepsin is a prescription medication used to treat a type of cancer called cutaneous T-cell lymphoma (CTCL) that has not responded to other treatments. It is a type of drug called a histone deacetylase (HDAC) inhibitor, which works by helping to slow or stop the growth of cancer cells. Romidepsin is typically given as an injection into a vein by a healthcare provider. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and report any potential side effects or concerns.

Ropeginterferon alfa-2b is a long-acting form of interferon alfa-2b, which is used in the treatment of certain types of cancers and viral infections. It is designed to have a longer duration of action in the body compared to standard interferon alfa-2b, allowing for less frequent dosing. It is important to consult with a healthcare provider for more information on its uses, side effects, and any other specific questions you may have about Ropeginterferon alfa-2b.

Rucaparib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of ovarian cancer. It belongs to a class of drugs known as PARP inhibitors, which work by blocking an enzyme called poly (ADP-ribose) polymerase (PARP) that cancer cells need to repair their DNA. This can help prevent cancer cells from growing and dividing. Rucaparib is typically used in patients with advanced ovarian cancer who have already received multiple lines of chemotherapy. It is important to consult with a healthcare provider for more information about Rucaparib, as it can have side effects and interactions with other medications.

Ruxolitinib is a medication used to treat certain types of blood disorders, specifically myelofibrosis and polycythemia vera. It works by inhibiting enzymes that are involved in the growth and development of abnormal blood cells. It is often prescribed for patients who have not responded to other treatments or who are not eligible for a bone marrow transplant. Like all medications, Ruxolitinib can have side effects, so it's important to discuss the risks and benefits with your healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Sacituzumab govitecan is a novel antibody-drug conjugate (ADC) used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as metastatic triple-negative breast cancer and metastatic urothelial cancer. It consists of an anti-Trop-2 antibody linked to a potent chemotherapy drug called SN-38. This ADC targets cancer cells that express Trop-2, a protein found on the surface of many types of cancer cells, delivering the chemotherapy directly to the cancer cells, which can help reduce systemic toxicity compared to traditional chemotherapy. It has shown promising results in clinical trials and has been approved for certain indications in some countries. As with any cancer therapy, it is important to discuss with a healthcare provider to determine if it is a suitable treatment option for an individual's specific condition.

Sargramostim is a man-made form of a protein that stimulates the growth of white blood cells in the body. It is used to help increase the production of white blood cells in patients who have undergone bone marrow transplantation, received chemotherapy, or have certain medical conditions. Sargramostim may also be used to treat certain types of infections. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's guidance on how to use Sargramostim safely and effectively.

Selinexor is a drug that belongs to a class of medications known as selective inhibitor of nuclear export (SINE) compounds. It is used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as multiple myeloma and diffuse large B-cell lymphoma. Selinexor works by blocking the mechanism that allows cancer cells to export tumor-suppressor proteins, leading to the accumulation of these proteins inside the cancer cells and ultimately causing them to die. As with any medication, there may be side effects and interactions with other drugs, so it is important to discuss with your healthcare provider before starting Selinexor.

Selumetinib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, specifically melanoma and non-small cell lung cancer. It works by inhibiting a specific protein (MEK) that is involved in cancer cell growth and survival. Selumetinib is typically used in combination with other cancer treatments and can have side effects such as nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, and skin rash. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of Selumetinib with a healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Semustine is a chemotherapy drug used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, including brain tumors and Hodgkin's lymphoma. It belongs to a class of medications known as alkylating agents, which work by interfering with the growth of cancer cells. Semustine is usually administered orally or intravenously, and its side effects may include nausea, vomiting, hair loss, and decreased blood cell counts. It is important to only use Semustine under the supervision of a healthcare provider experienced in the use of chemotherapy drugs.

Sipuleucel-T, also known by its brand name Provenge, is a therapeutic cancer vaccine used in the treatment of advanced prostate cancer. It is a personalized treatment, made by collecting a patient's own immune cells and modifying them to attack cancer cells. Sipuleucel-T has been shown to extend the survival of some patients with advanced prostate cancer and is typically used after other treatments have been unsuccessful. It is administered through a series of infusions and has been approved by the FDA for use in certain cases of advanced prostate cancer.

Sonidegib is a medication used to treat a type of skin cancer called basal cell carcinoma that has spread (metastasized) or cannot be treated with surgery or radiation therapy. It works by inhibiting a protein called smoothened, which plays a role in the growth of cancer cells. It comes in the form of a capsule and is typically taken once a day. As with any medication, it's important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and discuss any questions or concerns you may have.

Sorafenib is a medication used to treat certain types of cancer, including advanced kidney cancer and liver cancer. It works by slowing or stopping the growth of cancer cells in the body. Sorafenib is usually taken in the form of a pill and is often prescribed by oncologists as part of a comprehensive treatment plan for cancer patients. Like all medications, Sorafenib may have side effects, so it is important for patients to discuss potential risks and benefits with their healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Streptozocin is a chemotherapy medication used to treat certain types of cancer, such as pancreatic islet cell cancer (neuroendocrine tumors) and metastatic cancer of the pancreatic cells. It works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells in the body. It is usually administered by injection into a vein by a healthcare provider. Common side effects may include nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, and lowered white blood cell count. It is important to discuss with your doctor about the potential benefits and risks of using Streptozocin for your specific condition.

Sunitinib is a prescription medication used to treat certain types of cancer, including kidney cancer and gastrointestinal stromal tumor (GIST). It works by blocking the action of proteins that promote the growth and spread of cancer cells. Sunitinib is taken orally, usually once a day on an empty stomach. Like all medications, it can cause side effects, so it's important to talk to your doctor about the risks and benefits before starting treatment with sunitinib.

Tagraxofusp is a medication used for the treatment of blastic plasmacytoid dendritic cell neoplasm (BPDCN), a rare and aggressive type of blood cancer. It is a targeted therapy that works by binding to a protein on the surface of cancer cells, leading to cell death. Tagraxofusp is administered through intravenous infusion and is typically used in patients who have not responded to other treatments or have relapsed. Like all medications, it may have side effects, so it's important to discuss the risks and benefits with a healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Talazoparib is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of breast cancer, specifically those caused by mutations in the BRCA genes. It belongs to a class of drugs known as PARP inhibitors, which work by interfering with the ability of cancer cells to repair their DNA. Talazoparib is typically used in patients with advanced or metastatic breast cancer who have already received prior treatment. As with any medication, it is important to discuss potential benefits and risks with your healthcare provider.

Talimogene laherparepvec, also known as T-VEC, is an oncolytic virus therapy approved by the FDA for the treatment of melanoma skin cancer. It works by using a modified herpes simplex virus to selectively target and kill cancer cells while stimulating the body's immune response against the tumor. T-VEC is typically injected directly into the tumor, where it replicates and destroys cancer cells. It has shown promising results in some patients, but like any treatment, it may not be suitable for everyone and can have side effects. It is important to consult with a healthcare provider to determine if T-VEC is a suitable option for individual cases.

Tamibarotene is a synthetic retinoid used for the treatment of acute promyelocytic leukemia (APL), a type of cancer affecting the bone marrow and blood. It works by inducing differentiation and maturation of leukemia cells. Tamibarotene is used in conjunction with other chemotherapy agents and is typically prescribed by oncologists for patients with APL. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's recommendations and guidance when taking Tamibarotene.

Tamoxifen is a medication commonly used to treat breast cancer. It is a type of hormone therapy that works by blocking the effects of estrogen in the breast tissue, which can help slow or stop the growth of cancer cells. Tamoxifen is often prescribed to women with hormone receptor-positive breast cancer, and may also be used to reduce the risk of developing breast cancer in high-risk individuals. Like all medications, Tamoxifen can have side effects, so it is important to discuss with a healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Tegafur gimeracil oteracil is a combination drug used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, specifically colorectal cancer. It combines three active ingredients - tegafur, gimeracil, and oteracil. Tegafur is a prodrug of fluorouracil, a chemotherapy medication that inhibits the growth of cancer cells. Gimeracil enhances the anti-cancer effects of fluorouracil by preventing its quick breakdown in the body. Oteracil helps reduce the gastrointestinal toxicity associated with fluorouracil, making the medication more tolerable for patients. This combination therapy is used in the adjuvant treatment of stage III colon cancer. It is important to discuss with a healthcare professional about the potential benefits and side effects of this medication before starting treatment.

Tegafur is a prodrug that gets metabolized in the body into 5-fluorouracil (5-FU), which is a chemotherapy medication. 5-FU is an anti-cancer agent that inhibits the growth of cancer cells by interfering with their ability to divide and multiply. Uracil is a nucleic acid base that is a component of RNA. When Tegafur is combined with uracil, it enhances the activity of 5-FU and improves its effectiveness as a cancer treatment. This combination therapy is often used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as colorectal cancer.

Temozolomide is a chemotherapy drug used in the treatment of certain types of brain tumors, specifically glioblastoma multiforme and anaplastic astrocytoma. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Temozolomide is usually taken orally as a capsule and is often used in combination with radiation therapy. Like all chemotherapy drugs, it can have side effects, including nausea, vomiting, fatigue, and a decrease in blood cell counts. It is important to discuss any potential side effects and concerns with your healthcare provider before starting treatment with temozolomide.

Temsirolimus is a medication that is used in the treatment of advanced renal cell carcinoma, a type of kidney cancer. It belongs to a class of drugs called mTOR inhibitors, which work by interfering with the growth of cancer cells. Temsirolimus is typically administered intravenously under medical supervision. It is important to consult with a healthcare provider for more information about Temsirolimus, including its potential side effects and interactions with other medications.

Teniposide is a chemotherapy medication used to treat certain types of cancer, such as leukemia and various solid tumors. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Teniposide is typically given in a hospital setting by a healthcare professional. Like any medication, it may cause side effects, so it is important to discuss the potential risks and benefits with your healthcare provider before starting treatment with teniposide.

Thalidomide is a medication that was developed in the 1950s and was initially prescribed as a sedative and anti-nausea drug for pregnant women. However, it was later discovered that thalidomide caused severe birth defects in babies whose mothers had taken the medication during pregnancy. The most common birth defects associated with thalidomide use include limb malformations, leading to the term "thalidomide babies." As a result of this devastating outcome, thalidomide was withdrawn from the market in the early 1960s and is now strictly regulated for certain medical conditions, such as multiple myeloma and leprosy.

Thioguanine is a medication primarily used to treat certain types of cancer, such as leukemia. It belongs to a class of medications known as antimetabolites, which work by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Thioguanine is typically taken orally in tablet form, and it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when taking this medication to ensure its effectiveness and reduce the risk of side effects. Like all medications, Thioguanine can have potential side effects, so it is essential to discuss any concerns or questions with your healthcare provider.

Thiotepa is a chemotherapy medication used to treat various types of cancer, including breast, bladder, and ovarian cancer. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Thiotepa is usually given as an injection or infusion under the supervision of a healthcare provider in a hospital or clinic setting. Like all chemotherapy drugs, Thiotepa can have side effects, which may include nausea, vomiting, hair loss, and a decreased ability to fight infections. It is important to discuss the potential risks and benefits of Thiotepa with your healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Tisagenlecleucel, also known by the brand name Kymriah, is a type of personalized cancer treatment known as CAR-T cell therapy. It is used to treat certain types of blood cancers, such as certain types of leukemia and lymphoma. Tisagenlecleucel works by modifying a patient's own immune cells to better recognize and attack cancer cells. It has shown promising results in some patients, but like any medical treatment, it can have side effects and may not be suitable for everyone. It is important to talk to your healthcare provider to see if Tisagenlecleucel is a good option for your specific situation.

Tivozanib is a tyrosine kinase inhibitor medication that is currently being studied for use in the treatment of advanced renal cell carcinoma (kidney cancer). It works by blocking the action of certain proteins in cancer cells, which may help slow down or stop the growth of the tumor. Clinical trials have shown promising results for tivozanib, but it is not yet approved for widespread use as of now. It's always best to consult with a healthcare professional for more specific and up-to-date information on this medication.

Topotecan is a prescription medication used to treat certain types of cancer, including ovarian cancer, lung cancer, and cervical cancer. It belongs to a class of medications known as topoisomerase inhibitors, which work by interfering with the DNA in cancer cells, preventing them from growing and spreading. Topotecan is typically given as an injection into a vein by a healthcare provider in a hospital or clinic setting. It is important to follow your doctor's instructions carefully when taking this medication, as it can cause side effects and may interact with other medications.

Toremifene is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as selective estrogen receptor modulators (SERMs). It is used to treat certain types of breast cancer by blocking the effects of estrogen in the body. Toremifene is often prescribed for women with advanced breast cancer that has spread to other parts of the body, as well as for reducing the risk of breast cancer recurrence. It is usually taken in tablet form and can have potential side effects, so it is essential to discuss with your healthcare provider before starting this medication.

Tositumomab is a monoclonal antibody used in combination with I-131 (radioactive iodine) for the treatment of certain types of non-Hodgkin's lymphoma. This combination therapy works by targeting and delivering radiation directly to cancer cells, which helps to destroy the cancer cells while minimizing damage to surrounding healthy tissues. It is typically used in patients who have not responded to other treatments or have relapsed after previous therapy. It is important to consult with a healthcare provider for more detailed information and to discuss potential risks and benefits of this treatment.

Trabectedin is a prescription medication used to treat certain types of soft tissue sarcomas, which are cancers that originate in the soft tissues of the body, such as muscles, fat, blood vessels, and tendons. Trabectedin works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. It is typically used when other treatments have not been effective or have stopped working. Trabectedin is given through an intravenous infusion and is usually administered in a clinical setting by a healthcare provider. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and side effects of Trabectedin with your healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Trametinib is a medication that belongs to a class of drugs known as kinase inhibitors. It is used to treat certain types of cancer, such as melanoma and non-small cell lung cancer, that have specific genetic mutations. Trametinib works by blocking the action of certain proteins in cancer cells, which can help slow down or stop the growth of the cancer. It is usually prescribed by a doctor and is taken orally in the form of a tablet. It is important to follow your doctor's instructions carefully when taking Trametinib and to report any side effects or concerns to your healthcare provider.

Tranexamic acid is a medication used to treat or prevent excessive bleeding. It works by helping to reduce the breakdown of blood clots in the body. It is commonly used in surgeries, heavy menstrual bleeding, and certain medical conditions where blood clotting may be a concern. It is available in various forms such as tablets, injections, and topical creams. As with any medication, it is important to use Tranexamic acid under the supervision of a healthcare professional.

Trastuzumab, also known by its trade name Herceptin, is a medication used to treat certain types of breast cancer and stomach cancer. It is a monoclonal antibody that targets and inhibits the HER2 protein, which is overexpressed in some cancer cells. Trastuzumab can help slow or stop the growth of cancer cells and improve outcomes for patients with HER2-positive cancers. It is typically given intravenously and may be used in combination with other cancer treatments. Like all medications, it can have side effects, so it's important for patients to be monitored closely by their healthcare providers while receiving trastuzumab.

Tremelimumab is a type of immunotherapy drug that belongs to a class of medications known as checkpoint inhibitors. It works by helping the immune system recognize and attack cancer cells. Tremelimumab has been investigated for its potential use in treating various types of cancer, including melanoma and mesothelioma. It is still undergoing clinical trials to determine its effectiveness and safety profile. As with any medical treatment, it's important to consult with a healthcare provider for personalized information and guidance.

Treosulfan is a medication used in conditioning treatment before a stem cell transplant. It is used to help prepare the body for receiving the transplanted cells by suppressing the immune system and making room for the new cells to grow. Treosulfan is also used in the treatment of certain types of cancers. It's important to use this medication only as prescribed by a healthcare professional and to closely follow their instructions.

Trifluridine and tipiracil is a combination medication used for the treatment of certain types of cancer, specifically metastatic colorectal cancer and gastric cancer. Trifluridine is a nucleoside analog and tipiracil is a thymidine phosphorylase inhibitor. This combination medication works by helping to stop the growth and spread of cancer cells. It is usually given orally in the form of tablets and should be taken as prescribed by a healthcare provider. Side effects may occur and it is important to discuss any concerns with a healthcare professional.

Triptorelin is a synthetic hormone used in medicine to treat conditions such as advanced prostate cancer, endometriosis, and precocious puberty. It works by decreasing the production of certain hormones in the body, ultimately alleviating symptoms of these conditions. Triptorelin is often administered as an injection under the skin or into a muscle by a healthcare professional. Like any medication, it can have side effects, so it is important to discuss any concerns with your healthcare provider.

Valproate is a medication that is commonly used to treat epilepsy, bipolar disorder, and migraines. It works by helping to balance certain natural substances in the brain that may be causing the conditions. It is important to take Valproate as prescribed by a healthcare provider, as it can have side effects and may interact with other medications. It is also important to have regular check-ups while taking Valproate to monitor its effectiveness and any potential side effects.

Valrubicin is a medication used in the treatment of bladder cancer. It is a chemotherapy drug that is administered directly into the bladder to treat early-stage bladder cancer that has not invaded the muscle layer of the bladder wall. Valrubicin works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the bladder. It is important to follow your doctor's instructions carefully when taking this medication and to report any side effects or concerns to them.

Vandetanib is a medication that is used to treat certain types of cancer, specifically medullary thyroid cancer. It works by blocking certain proteins in the body that help cancer cells grow and spread. Vandetanib is typically taken orally in the form of a tablet. Like all medications, Vandetanib can have potential side effects, so it's important to take it as prescribed by a healthcare provider and discuss any concerns with them.

Vemurafenib is a medication used for the treatment of certain types of skin cancer, specifically melanoma that has a specific genetic mutation known as BRAF V600. It works by targeting and inhibiting the activity of the mutated BRAF protein, which helps slow down or stop the growth of cancer cells. It is usually taken orally in the form of tablets. Like all medications, Vemurafenib may have potential side effects and interactions, so it's important to consult with a healthcare professional before using it.

Venetoclax is a medication that is used to treat chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL), small lymphocytic lymphoma (SLL), and acute myeloid leukemia (AML) in certain patients. It works by targeting and blocking a protein called B-cell lymphoma-2 (BCL-2), which helps cancer cells survive. Venetoclax is typically prescribed by healthcare professionals and should be taken as directed to achieve the best results. As with any medication, it may have side effects, so it's important to talk to your doctor about any concerns or questions you may have.

Vinblastine is a chemotherapy medication that is used to treat certain types of cancer, including Hodgkin's disease, non-Hodgkin's lymphoma, and certain types of leukemia. It works by stopping the growth of cancer cells in the body. Vinblastine is typically given as an injection into a vein by a healthcare provider in a hospital or clinic setting. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions carefully when taking vinblastine, as it can cause side effects such as nausea, vomiting, hair loss, and low blood cell counts.

Vincristine is a type of chemotherapy medication commonly used to treat various types of cancers, including leukemia, lymphoma, and solid tumors. It works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells, ultimately helping to stop their spread in the body. Vincristine is usually given by injection into a vein and is often part of combination chemotherapy regimens. Like all medications, Vincristine can cause side effects, such as nerve damage, constipation, hair loss, and decreased blood cell counts. It is important to discuss potential risks and benefits with your healthcare provider before starting treatment with Vincristine.

Vincristine liposomal is a medication used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as leukemia and lymphoma. It is a liposomal formulation of vincristine, which is a chemotherapy drug that works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells. Vincristine liposomal is typically given intravenously by a healthcare provider in a hospital or medical setting. As with any medication, it may have side effects, so it is important to discuss the potential risks and benefits with your healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Vindesine is a type of chemotherapy drug used to treat various types of cancer, including certain types of leukemia, lymphoma, and lung cancer. It belongs to a class of medications known as vinca alkaloids, which work by interfering with the growth of cancer cells. Vindesine is typically administered intravenously by a healthcare provider in a hospital or clinic setting. Like all chemotherapy drugs, Vindesine can have side effects, including nausea, vomiting, hair loss, and decreased blood cell counts. It is important to discuss the potential risks and benefits of Vindesine treatment with your healthcare provider.

Vinflunine is a type of chemotherapy drug that is used in the treatment of advanced or metastatic transitional cell carcinoma of the urothelial tract. It works by disrupting the growth of cancer cells. Vinflunine is typically administered intravenously and may be used when other chemotherapy agents have not been effective. As with any chemotherapy drug, there can be side effects, and it is important to discuss any concerns with a healthcare provider.

Vinorelbine is a type of chemotherapy drug that is used to treat various types of cancer, including lung cancer, breast cancer, and non-Hodgkin's lymphoma. It works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells, ultimately slowing down or stopping their ability to spread. Vinorelbine is typically administered intravenously by a healthcare provider in a clinical setting. It is important to discuss the potential side effects and benefits of Vinorelbine with your healthcare team before beginning treatment.

Vismodegib is a medication used to treat basal cell carcinoma, a type of skin cancer. It works by inhibiting a specific protein pathway that is important for the growth of cancer cells. It is typically used for treating locally advanced basal cell carcinoma or metastatic basal cell carcinoma that has spread to other parts of the body. As with any medication, it is important to follow your doctor's instructions and discuss any potential side effects or concerns.

Vorinostat is a medication commonly used in the treatment of cutaneous T-cell lymphoma, a type of non-Hodgkin lymphoma. It is a type of drug known as a histone deacetylase inhibitor, which works by interfering with the growth of cancer cells. Vorinostat is typically taken orally in capsule form and can have side effects such as fatigue, nausea, and diarrhea. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions when taking Vorinostat and to report any side effects experienced during treatment.

Zidovudine is an antiretroviral medication used to treat HIV/AIDS. It works by preventing the replication of the virus in the body. It is commonly used in combination with other medications to manage HIV infection. Like all medications, zidovudine can have side effects and should be taken as prescribed by a healthcare provider.

Ziv-aflibercept is a medication used for the treatment of certain types of cancer, specifically metastatic colorectal cancer, metastatic prostate cancer, and certain types of advanced ovarian cancer. It works by blocking the growth of blood vessels that supply nutrients to tumors, thereby reducing their growth and spread. Ziv-aflibercept is typically given intravenously under the supervision of a healthcare provider. Like all medications, it can have potential side effects, so it's important to discuss the risks and benefits with your doctor before starting treatment.

Capmatinib, also known by its brand name Tabrecta, is a medication used to treat a type of non-small cell lung cancer called MET exon 14 skipping mutation-positive metastatic NSCLC. It is a targeted therapy that works by inhibiting specific proteins involved in the growth and spread of cancer cells. Capmatinib is usually taken in the form of oral tablets and is available by prescription under the supervision of a healthcare provider. Like all medications, capmatinib may have side effects, so it's important to discuss any concerns or questions with a healthcare professional.

Enfortumab vedotin is a type of targeted therapy used in the treatment of locally advanced or metastatic urothelial cancer. It works by targeting and attacking cancer cells that have a specific protein (Nectin-4) on their surface. Enfortumab vedotin is typically used in patients who have previously received platinum-containing chemotherapy and an immune checkpoint inhibitor. It is administered through intravenous infusion and may have side effects such as fatigue, hair loss, and peripheral neuropathy. It's important to consult with a healthcare provider for personalized information and guidance on Enfortumab vedotin treatment.

Trastuzumab deruxtecan is a medication used for the treatment of certain types of cancer, including HER2-positive breast cancer and gastric cancer. It is a type of antibody-drug conjugate that combines an antibody called trastuzumab with a chemotherapy drug called deruxtecan. This combination helps deliver the chemotherapy directly to cancer cells that express the HER2 protein, which can help improve its effectiveness and reduce side effects compared to traditional chemotherapy. It is important to consult with a healthcare provider for more information about Trastuzumab deruxtecan, including potential side effects, dosage, and administration.

Abarelix is a type of medication that belongs to a class of drugs called gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH) antagonists. It is used in the treatment of advanced prostate cancer. Abarelix works by blocking the production of certain hormones that can stimulate the growth of cancer cells in the prostate. It helps to slow down the progression of the cancer and alleviate symptoms associated with prostate cancer. Belantamab mafodotin is a monoclonal antibody-drug conjugate (ADC) used in the treatment of multiple myeloma, a type of cancer that affects plasma cells in the bone marrow. It works by targeting and delivering a chemotherapy drug directly to the cancer cells, helping to kill them while sparing healthy cells. Belantamab mafodotin has shown promising results in clinical trials and has been approved for use in certain cases of relapsed or refractory multiple myeloma. As with any medication, it is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks with your healthcare provider.

Tucatinib is a prescription medication used in the treatment of HER2-positive breast cancer that has spread to other parts of the body. It works by blocking a protein called HER2, which can help slow down or stop the growth of cancer cells. This medication is typically used in combination with other cancer treatments. As with any medication, it is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions carefully and discuss any potential side effects or concerns.

Daratumumab is a monoclonal antibody medication that targets a protein called CD38, which is commonly found on the surface of myeloma cells. This medication is used to treat multiple myeloma, a type of cancer that affects a type of white blood cell called plasma cells. It works by helping the immune system to identify and attack the cancer cells.

Hyaluronidase is an enzyme that is commonly used in combination with certain medications to help them spread and penetrate tissues more effectively. When hyaluronidase is used with medications like daratumumab, it helps the medication to be absorbed more quickly into the body, which can improve the effectiveness of the treatment.

Alitretinoin, also known as Toctino, is a prescription medication used to treat severe chronic hand eczema in adults. It is a retinoid that works by regulating skin cell production and reducing inflammation. Alitretinoin is usually taken in the form of capsules and should be used as directed by a healthcare provider. Common side effects may include dry skin, headache, and rash. It is important to discuss any potential risks and benefits of alitretinoin with a healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Brexucabtagene autoleucel, also known by its brand name Tecartus, is a type of chimeric antigen receptor (CAR) T-cell therapy used to treat certain types of blood cancers, such as mantle cell lymphoma. It involves genetically modifying a patient's own T cells to help identify and attack cancer cells. This therapy has shown promising results in clinical trials for patients who have not responded to other treatments. It is important to consult with a healthcare provider for more information on the use and potential side effects of brexucabtagene autoleucel.

Alpelisib is a medication used to treat a certain type of breast cancer that is hormone receptor-positive and human epidermal growth factor receptor 2 (HER2)-negative. It belongs to a class of drugs known as PI3K inhibitors and works by blocking the action of an abnormal protein that promotes the growth of cancer cells. Alpelisib is typically used in combination with another medication called fulvestrant and may be prescribed by your healthcare provider for the treatment of advanced breast cancer. It is important to follow your doctor's instructions and discuss any questions or concerns you may have about this medication.

Amonafide is a synthetic compound that was under investigation as a potential anti-cancer agent. It belongs to a class of drugs known as DNA intercalators, which work by inserting themselves between the base pairs of DNA strands. However, development of Amonafide as a cancer treatment has been limited due to concerns about its side effects and efficacy. It is important to consult with a healthcare professional for the most up-to-date information on Amonafide or any other cancer treatments.

Amoxicillin is a commonly prescribed antibiotic used to treat a variety of bacterial infections, such as respiratory tract infections, ear infections, urinary tract infections, and skin infections. Aumolertinib is a targeted therapy medication used to treat non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC) that has specific mutations in the epidermal growth factor receptor (EGFR) gene. It works by blocking the activity of the mutated EGFR protein, which helps to slow down or stop the growth of cancer cells. Pemigatinib is a prescription medication used for the treatment of certain types of cancer, specifically cholangiocarcinoma (bile duct cancer) that has a specific genetic mutation called FGFR2 fusion or rearrangement. It is a targeted therapy that works by blocking the activity of the FGFR protein, which can help slow down or stop the growth of cancer cells. Ripretinib, also known by its brand name Qinlock, is a medication used to treat certain types of gastrointestinal stromal tumors (GIST) that cannot be surgically removed or have spread to other parts of the body. Ripretinib was approved by the FDA in 2020 for the treatment of advanced GIST in adults. Selpercatinib is a targeted therapy medication used to treat specific kinds of cancer, such as non-small cell lung cancer, medullary thyroid cancer, and other types of cancer with certain gene mutations. It works by blocking specific proteins that drive the growth of cancer cells. It is important to talk to your healthcare provider for more information about selpercatinib, including its possible side effects and benefits.

Decitabine is a medication used in the treatment of myelodysplastic syndromes (MDS), a group of conditions where the bone marrow does not produce enough healthy blood cells. It works by helping the bone marrow to produce normal blood cells.

Cedazuridine is a newer medication that is combined with decitabine to improve its effectiveness. Cedazuridine helps the body process and absorb decitabine more efficiently, leading to better treatment outcomes.

Both decitabine and cedazuridine are prescription medications and should only be used under the guidance of a healthcare provider. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions carefully when taking these medications.

Bismuth subsalicylate is a medication that is commonly used to treat symptoms of upset stomach, heartburn, indigestion, and diarrhea. It works by coating the stomach lining and reducing irritation and inflammation. It is also known for its antimicrobial properties, which help to alleviate symptoms of gastrointestinal infections. However, it is important to follow the recommended dosage and consult a healthcare professional before using this medication, as misuse can lead to potential side effects.

Camrelizumab is a monoclonal antibody that targets and inhibits a protein called PD-1 (programmed cell death protein 1). It is used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as classical Hodgkin's lymphoma, non-small cell lung cancer, and esophageal cancer. Camrelizumab works by blocking the interaction between PD-1 on T cells and PD-L1 on cancer cells, which helps the immune system to recognize and attack the cancer cells. It is generally well-tolerated, but like all medications, it can have side effects. It is important to discuss the potential benefits and risks of camrelizumab with a healthcare provider before starting treatment.

Relugolix is a drug used for the treatment of advanced prostate cancer, uterine fibroids, and endometriosis. It works by lowering the levels of certain hormones in the body that can contribute to the growth of these conditions. It is available in oral tablet form and is typically used under the supervision of a healthcare provider. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions while taking Relugolix and to report any side effects or concerns during treatment.

Elacestrant is an investigational new drug being studied for the treatment of breast cancer. It belongs to a class of medications known as selective estrogen receptor degraders (SERDs), which work by blocking the activity of estrogen in breast cancer cells. Clinical trials are currently ongoing to determine its efficacy and safety in treating various types of breast cancer.

Trimetrexate is a drug used in cancer treatment and is specifically classified as an antifolate. It works by disrupting folate metabolism in cancer cells, which are essential for cell division and growth. Trimetrexate is typically used in combination with other medications in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as ovarian cancer and certain leukemias. As with any medication, it is important to use Trimetrexate only under the supervision and prescription of a qualified healthcare professional.

Tepotinib is a medication used for the treatment of certain types of lung cancer, specifically non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC) that has a specific genetic mutation called MET exon 14 skipping alteration. It works by targeting and blocking the MET receptor tyrosine kinase, which is involved in the growth and spread of cancer cells. Tepotinib is typically used in patients whose cancer has progressed despite other treatments or who are not candidates for surgery. Futibatinib is an investigational drug being developed for the treatment of advanced solid tumors. It belongs to a class of drugs known as selective fibroblast growth factor receptor (FGFR) inhibitors. Futibatinib works by targeting specific genetic mutations that may drive the growth of certain cancers. Clinical trials are ongoing to evaluate the safety and effectiveness of Futibatinib in different types of tumors. The NovoTTF-100A system, also known as Optune, is a medical device used for the treatment of glioblastoma multiforme (GBM), a type of brain cancer. Optune works by delivering low-intensity electric fields, called tumor-treating fields (TTF), to the brain to disrupt the division of cancer cells and potentially slow or stop tumor growth. It is typically used in combination with other standard treatments for GBM, such as chemotherapy and radiation therapy. Before using Optune, it is important to consult with a healthcare provider to determine if it is an appropriate treatment option for the individual's specific condition.

Lisocabtagene maraleucel, also known as Liso-cel, is a type of chimeric antigen receptor (CAR) T-cell therapy used in the treatment of certain types of blood cancers, such as certain types of non-Hodgkin lymphoma. It works by modifying a patient's own T-cells to recognize and attack cancer cells. Liso-cel has shown promising results in clinical trials and has been approved by the FDA for certain indications. Idecabtagene vicleucel, also known as ide-cel or Abecma, is a type of CAR-T cell therapy used to treat certain types of blood cancers, such as multiple myeloma. It is a personalized treatment where a patient's immune cells are modified in a laboratory to better recognize and attack cancer cells when infused back into the body. Idecabtagene vicleucel has shown promising results in clinical trials for patients who have not responded to other treatments, and it has been approved for use in certain cases. Avapritinib is a medication used to treat certain types of tumors, such as gastrointestinal stromal tumors (GIST) and systemic mastocytosis. Avapritinib may be prescribed by a healthcare provider in certain situations where other treatments have not been effective. Pexidartinib is a prescription medication used for the treatment of symptomatic tenosynovial giant cell tumors (TGCT) in adults. It works by blocking certain enzymes that are involved in the growth of tumors. This medication is available in capsule form and should be taken exactly as prescribed by a healthcare provider. Pralsetinib is a targeted therapy used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as non-small cell lung cancer or thyroid cancer, that have specific genetic mutations. It works by blocking the activity of certain proteins that promote cancer cell growth. Pralsetinib is typically prescribed by a healthcare provider and requires careful monitoring for potential side effects. It's important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and discuss any questions or concerns you may have about this medication.

Lurbinectedin is a type of chemotherapy medication that is used to treat certain types of cancer, specifically small cell lung cancer. It works by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body. Lurbinectedin is typically given through intravenous infusion and may be used in combination with other cancer treatments. Metronidazole is an antibiotic and antiprotozoal medication used to treat various bacterial and parasitic infections in the body. Naxitamab, also known as Danyelza, is a medication used for the treatment of neuroblastoma, a type of cancer that mostly affects children. Tetracycline is an antibiotic commonly used to treat a variety of bacterial infections, such as acne, urinary tract infections, and respiratory tract infections. Tripotassium dicitratobismuthate is a compound that has been used in the past as an antidiarrheal medication. Belzutifan, also known as MK-6482, is an investigational drug developed by Merck for the treatment of certain types of cancer. Amivantamab is a targeted therapy used in the treatment of non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC). Azacitidine is a medication primarily used to treat a type of blood cancer called myelodysplastic syndrome (MDS) and certain types of leukemia. Colchicine is a medication that is primarily used to treat gout and familial Mediterranean fever. Dostarlimab is a type of cancer treatment known as an immune checkpoint inhibitor. Dostarlimab is used in the treatment of certain types of cancer, such as endometrial cancer or dMMR/MSI-H solid tumors. Semplulimab is a monoclonal antibody that is being studied for its potential use in treating autoimmune diseases such as alopecia areata and inflammatory bowel disease. Sugemalimab, also known as CS1003, is an investigational anti-PD-L1 monoclonoclonal antibody being developed by CStone Pharmaceuticals for the treatment of various types of cancer. Sirolimus protein-bound particles refer to a formulation of the medication sirolimus, which is used to prevent the body from rejecting organ transplants. Suramin is a medication used to treat a few different conditions, such as African sleeping sickness (trypanosomiasis) and river blindness (onchocerciasis). Adagrasib, also known as MRTX849, is an investigational drug being developed by Mirati Therapeutics for the treatment of certain types of solid tumors, particularly those with KRAS G12C mutations. Tebentafusp is a novel immunotherapy treatment that is being developed for the treatment of metastatic uveal melanoma, a rare and aggressive form of eye cancer. Fedratinib is a medication that is used to treat a certain type of bone marrow disorder called myelofibrosis. Trastuzumab and hyaluronidase is a medication used to treat HER2-positive breast cancer.
